title: popovers
directions: Beat milk, flour and oil for 1 minute.
Beat eggs (one at a time) and salt into this mixture.
Pour into greased cupcake or muffin pans.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Makes 30.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Combine flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.

Mix just until blended after each addition. Stir in vanilla, 1 1/3 cups chocolate morsels and grated chocolate. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy; gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes; cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Make a glaze out of confectioners sugar and milk. Spoon over warm cake.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate morsels.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in oven-safe casserole dish.
In small mixing bowl, add sour cream, Ranch dressing, bacon bits, parsley and 1/4 to 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Pour sour cream mixture over potatoes.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add corn flakes and mix until well coated with butter.
Sprinkle corn flakes and remaining cheese over potato mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Combine sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool milk to lukewarm after adding to sugar mixture.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add this to milk, sugar mixture.
Beat eggs and add.
Add half of flour and beat until smooth.
Add remainder of flour and mix until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and let rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Punch down and make out into rolls.
Let rolls rise.
Bake at 350°.
May let dough rise in refrigerator overnight if desired.

title: grandma campbell's butterscotch pudding and pie filling
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and butter. Stir constantly over medium heat until filling thickens and boils. Remove from heat and cool. Pour into prepared crust and top with meringue.

title: catherine babcock's crust and old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, lard and salt together; add 1/2 cup water. Form into a ball and roll.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 eight-inch pie crusts or 1 large deep-dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (45 minutes for large pie).
Pecans may be placed on top of pies before baking.

title: pastel de tres leches(cake with three milks)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9X13 pan. Sift flour and baking soda together; set aside.
Cream together butter and 1 c. sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and 1/2 tsp. vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture 2 tablespoons at a time, mixing well until blended.
Pour into prepared cake pan and bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and poke with fork or skewer 8-10 times and let cool.
Mix milk, evaporated milk, condensed milk and liqueur and pour over cake.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
For frosting, mix whipping cream, 1 tsp. vanilla and 1 c. sugar, whipping until thick.
Spread over top of cake.
Store in refrigerator.
You can add cherries, blueberries, raspberries, apples or peaches in the amount of 1/2 c. to the batter.
You can also add chocolate syrup to the milk mixture or add white chocolate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; season and drain.
In bowl, soak corn tortillas with enchilada sauce.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with layer of tortillas.
Layer ground beef.
Mix cheeses and egg.
Layer cheese, sauce, tortillas and beef until ingredients are used.
Top with tortillas, covered with sauce. Small amount of water may be added to sauce for moistness.

title: butterfinger candy pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in water, sugar, flour and salt until well combined.
Melt butter in a small pan over low heat, then stir hot butter into batter.
Stir in 6 chopped candy bars.
Cool completely. (Can be made ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours.)
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell until golden and cool on rack.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Pour cooled filling into shell and bake 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with whipped cream and remaining 2 chopped candy bars around edge.
Makes 10 servings.

title: party dip
directions: Mix and chill. Please follow these directions carefully.

Some people have been known to confuse the amount of garlic with the amount of bacon chips. That's okay if you like a lot of garlic. But it's a lot better just using 1/4 teaspoon garlic instead of 1/4 cup.

title: beef stew
directions: Cube beef in bite size pieces.
Flour and brown in skillet. Season with garlic salt and cloves while browning.
Fill stew pot, Dutch oven, 1/2 with water and 1 teaspoon bouillon.
Dice onions and combine with beef.
Let simmer for 2 or 3 hours. Add cut carrots and potatoes into bite size pieces.
Add 1/2 stick butter and simmer until vegetables are fully cooked.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add peanut butter and powdered sugar. Blend in Cool Whip.
Blend well and put in graham cracker crust.

title: patsy's stuffed pork chops
directions: Crumble the cornbread in a large bowl; set aside.
Melt the margarine on low heat in a medium-sized frying pan.
Saute onions and celery in the melted margarine until tender and onions are transparent.
Add to the cornbread.
Add eggs, sage and water. Mix well with your hands.
Use mixture to stuff pork chops.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Mix soups together.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover tightly with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for about one hour.
May use chicken breasts instead of whole chicken, if desired.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls flat onto large baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Mix the softened cream cheese, mayo and dry Ranch dressing.
Spread over cooled crust.
(May cut little squares if preferred before topping with vegetables.)
Cut up vegetables into tiny, bite size pieces.
Spread over top.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Chill until jelled and serve.

title: hobo potatoes
directions: Tear off 2 pieces of heavy duty foil, about 18 inches each. Place one piece of foil on top of the other, then place sliced potatoes and chopped onion in center.

Sprinkle with salt, herbs, garlic powder and pepper, toss to mix and dot with bits of butter. Bring two long sides of foil together, over food and fold edges over several times, to seal but allowing space inside for steam. Fold short ends up and pinch together to seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Add 1/4 cup water to dry ingredients; stir until smooth.
Add egg yolks; stir again, then add the rest of water and stir well.
Place in double boiler; cook until thickens.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and margarine; stir well and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour on top of pie.
Bake in oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: orange pineapple jellied salad
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Add orange sherbet.
Let stand in refrigerator until nearly thick.
Beat with electric mixer to dissolve any bits of cream cheese which did not melt.
Add pineapple and oranges and fold in whipped cream.
Store in refrigerator.
You can put in an 8 or 9-inch glass square baking dish or Tupperware mold.

title: pre-game barbecue
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over roast.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes per pound of meat.
Cool, cut fat and bone from roast; break meat into bite size pieces.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Reheat meat and sauce until hot.
Serve on onion buns.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: diana's stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in pan. Saute garlic. Fry chicken until all pink is gone. Remove from pan. Cook vegetables in water in same pan until crisp-tender. Add ginger. Mix Yoshida's sauce with approximately 1 tablespoon cornstarch to thicken. Pour into pan. Add chicken. Heat. If too thick, add more water to thin. Serve over rice.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Stir rice, sauteed onion and beef consomme all together. Place rice mixture in baking dish.
Place pork chops on top. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken barley soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove chicken, let cool enough to handle, then remove bones and skin and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cool broth and skim off fat.
Return chicken to kettle and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for at least 1 hour or until vegetables and barley are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Yield: 5 servings.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Melt margarine, stir in sugar and syrup.
Boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Pour over all other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: taco salad(serves 6)
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper over medium heat; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, refried beans and canned tomatoes; simmer for 15 minutes.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes and avocado; toss.
Place lettuce mixture on individual serving plates.
Top with meat mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream and a tablespoon of sliced green onions, if desired.
Serve with corn chips.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven
to
400°. Grease a small baking dish with oleo. Wash
tomatoes
and
remove
stems and pulp, leaving 1/4 inch shells.
Chop removed pulp and beat in butter with onion, green pepper
and parsley, about 3 minutes.
Add bread crumbs, meat, salt
and
pepper.
Stuff tomato shells with mixture and place in baking
dish.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Brush tomato shells with oleo when half baked.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook water, potatoes, onion, celery, parsley, bouillon cubes, salt & pepper for 20 minutes.
Mix flour and milk and cook in separate pan until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add to potato mixture.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together, except noodles.
Pack in large pan.
Top with noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant.
Dip into egg and flour.
Brown in nonstick pan sprayed with Pam (brown slowly).
Saute onion and green peppers in nonstick pan.
Salt as desired.
Layer into casserole dish with tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. You may layer with cheese, but this makes more calories.

title: fruit pizza platters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 12-inch pizza pans. Combine 1/2 cake mix (dry), water, eggs, butter and brown sugar in a mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Blend in remaining cake mix.
Fold in nuts.
Divide batter evenly between the prepared pans.
Bake for 12 minutes.
After pizzas have cooled, spread Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture on both.
Arrange fruits in circular pattern over topping.
Start with the strawberries on outer edge, then pineapple wedges, grapes, banana slices and end with a reserved whole strawberry in the center.
Brush with the Apricot Glaze and refrigerate until serving.

title: pressed beef cheese ball
directions: Form all but last ingredient into ball.
Roll in pecans or sprinkle with paprika, whatever you want!

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, combine the broth, water, tomatoes, onion, garlic, celery, carrots and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the corn, zucchini and parsley and continue to simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
Adjust the seasonings and serve hot with a light sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sausage-macaroni fry
directions: Cook until vegetables are done.

title: broiled tomatoes with mushroom sauce
directions: Dissolve beef bouillon in water; set aside.
Saute mushrooms in butter in a heavy skillet until tender.
Stir in wine.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add bouillon.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thick and bubbly.
Keep warm while broiling tomatoes.
Remove stems from tomatoes; cut in half crosswise.

title: oven stew
directions: Bake for 5 hours at 275°.
Do not lift lid while baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cream oleo.
Pour over crackers.
Put in bottom of casserole bowl; saving enough for top.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup and milk together.
Put chicken on the cracker crumbs.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with rest of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 45 minutes.

title: taffy apple cookies
directions: Melt caramels and milk in a double boiler.
Dip cookies in to caramels, then into ground nuts.
Place in midget baking cups. Makes about 75 cookies.

title: seafood spread
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: low-fat crab dip
directions: In large saucepan, mix all ingredients together.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Serve warm with fat-free crackers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve box of jello in 1 cup hot water; add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and let partially set.
Stir in carrots and drained pineapple.
Prepare 1 package Dream Whip with 1/2 cup milk and fold into first mixture.
Store in refrigerator in covered dish.

title: baked acorn squash with apples
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Wash squash; cut in half and scoop out seeds and membrane.
Place squash, cut side down, in pan.
Add 1/2 cup water to pan.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 45 minutes or until tender.
(Done when fork can pierce skin and flesh easily.)

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa into a bowl. Stir in milk and melted shortening. Mix until smooth. Add nuts. Spread batter in greased 8-inch square pan. Mix brown sugar with remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over top of batter. Pour hot water over entire batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool slightly on wire rack. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Invert squares on plate and dip sauce from pan over each.

title: butter crisp ice cream
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; stir in butter.
Spoon mixture into a 15 x 19 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool; set aside.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and beaten egg yolks. Gradually add lime juice. Fill pie shell with the mixture. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not allow to brown. Chill for at least 2 hours. Whip the cream and garnish the chilled pie with a rosette of whipped cream before serving. Serves 8.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Add soup, grated cheese (reserve some for topping), carrot, onion, sour cream and spices.
Add melted butter to stuffing mix.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer the zucchini mixture and stuffing mixture, ending with the stuffing mixture.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cool pineapple pie
directions: Combine ice cream, milk and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer set a low speed until blended.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze, covered, while preparing pineapple mixture. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of the syrup.
Combine the cornstarch and 1 TBSP. reserved syrup in a medium saucepan and mix well.
Add pineapple and remaining reserved syrup to cornstarch mixture and mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour.
Spread over ice-cream mixture.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: caribbean shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling, pineapple with its juice, sour cream and sugar in deep narrow bottom bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill about three hours.
May garnish with Cool Whip; add pineapple if desired.

title: hot alaska salmon melts
directions: Drain salmon; break into large chunks.
Add mayo, parsley, onion, pimento, lemon juice and pepper; toss gently to mix.
Fold in 1/2 cup cheese.
Spread about 1/4 cup mixture onto each slice of bread or onto muffins.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil about 6 inches from heat until cheese melts and tops are golden (3 to 4 minutes).
Makes 8 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend, then add cream and bouillon.
Stir constantly.
When it thickens, add sliced mushrooms, seafood and mustard.
Add a little of this mixture to well beaten egg; gradually add all mixture to egg.
Put in casserole or shells. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Place in oven for 20 minutes. Add all the sherry when mixing ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Brown the 1/2 cup sugar. Add
the milk and sugar. Cook to soft ball. Remove from heat and beat by hand till cooled. Add butter and nuts. Pour onto buttered pie plate or pan.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together the meat, eggs, salt, pepper and bread crumbs. Form into 1-inch meatballs, place on a cookie sheet and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Bake the meatballs for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fantasia fruit punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine lemon-flavored ice tea mix, water, concentrates and fresh fruit.
Just before serving, add club soda. Serve with ice.
Makes about 20 (5 ounce) servings.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese over low fire.
Mix together boiled shrimp, mayonnaise, onions, celery and unflavored gelatin (dissolved in 1/4 cup water).
After soup and cream cheese are blended together, add shrimp mixture.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: kids can make 'em bagels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water until foamy.
Combine all ingredients. Knead until dough no longer clings to hands (adding small amounts of flour to dough if needed); let dough rest 15 minutes, then shape into bagels.
Let them rise for 30 minutes, then drop gently into a large pot of boiling sugar water.
Flip the bagels in the water (still simmering) after 3 minutes.
Cook other sides 3 minutes as well.
Remove from pot, then bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli with mornay sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes or until almost tender.
Refresh under cold water.
Drain well.
In medium saucepan, saute onion in butter 3 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir constantly over low heat for 1 minute.
Add milk, whisking constantly.
Cook over medium-high heat, whisking constantly, for 5 minutes.
Mixture will thicken.
Stir in Swiss cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.

title: crunchy cornflake chicken
directions: Rinse and drain chicken pieces.
Dip one piece at a time into egg mixture, then coat with crushed cornflakes.
Place on broiler pan (already sprayed with cooking spray).
Coat all pieces, then season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (until no pink juice runs out).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream
sugar, eggs and oil.
Add water, dry ingredients and nuts
and
raisins.
Put in greased and floured pans (2/3 full). Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 or 3 loaves.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; then sifted dry ingredients, nuts, cherries and coconut. Drop from a teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Beat well and pour over warm potatoes, diced.
Warm potatoes make better salad.
Refrigerate to cool and flavor.

title: cheesy carbonara
directions: Toss fettuccine with combined remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese (optional).

title: jiffy stew
directions: Fry out all fat from sausage.
Brown hamburger balls after brushing with A.1. sauce.
In pot, add tomatoes, potatoes, vegetables, sausage, hamburger balls and seasonings.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In a 1 quart saucepan, melt butter, add flour and whisk together well.
Add thawed broccoli and stir well.
Drain canned mushroom pieces, add and stir well.
Slowly add chicken stock, stirring until all is added.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and stir well.
Add the parsley flakes, salt, cayenne and pepper sauce and stir well.
Bring back to a low simmer.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with corn chips or French bread pieces.

title: baked beans (kidney)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; top with strip of bacon and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Put onion and carrots in bottom of crock-pot or cooking pot. Cut chicken into strips and season with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour to coat.
Place chicken on top of onion and carrots. Combine remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Pour over top of chicken.
Cover and cook on high (crock-pot) or low (stove) for 3 to 4 hours.
Dish is done when carrots are very tender.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: scandinavian peach soup
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; let stand 20 minutes.
In pan, boil the next 4 ingredients, then reduce to simmer 1 minute. Stir in peaches and chill.
Serve with a dollop of your choice of cream.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and dry completely!
Combine last 3 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Fold grapes into mixture and pour into container.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: baked vegetables medley
directions: Slice yellow squash and zucchini in 1/4-inch rounds.
Dice onion and peppers.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle olive oil to coat vegetables.
Sprinkle onion powder and garlic powder.
Stir vegetables to coat well.
Bake in 350° oven until doneness you like.
Stir often.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and cream some more. Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each.
Alternate flour and milk, ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325°, starting with a cold oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk together until it gets thick. Mix butter and graham crackers together. Put crackers in pie pan. Pour lemon mixture into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: catsup
directions: Put tomatoes in
3-gallon
stone jar.
Put 1/2 cup salt on top of tomatoes.
Cover
with tea towel.
Let stand 3 days. Drain all liquid off, cook 10 minutes and run tomatoes through a colander. Pour tomato juice in pan.
Add vinegar and sugar. Put pickling spices and onions
in
a
cloth
bag and put into tomatoes.
Cook until thick.
Seal	in pint jars.
Makes 6 1/2 pints.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic.
Add sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, Italian seasoning, pepper and 1/8 cup parsley.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water, mashing the tomatoes. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring occasionally until thick, about 1 1/2 hours.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg, 1/8 cup parsley and salt, mixing well.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix chicken, celery, cooked rice, mayonnaise, mushrooms, onion, lemon juice, salt, soup and water chestnuts together; put in a casserole.
Melt butter or margarine; add nuts and flakes. Pour on top of mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry punch(serves 50)
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar with 1 gallon water.
Pour in remaining water and stir.
When ready to serve, pour in pineapple juice and uncola.
Pour 1 gallon into punch bowl and add crushed ice.

title: baked new england yams
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Line 10 x 6-inch baking dish with pineapple, overlapping some.
Arrange yams in center.
Pour syrup of yams.
Combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in margarine until it looks like fine crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over yams.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.
Broil for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix and bake in thin layers.
Put blackberry jelly between layers.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Add all dry ingredients together and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients stirring only until moistened. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of 9-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle cinnamon and 1/2 cup of the sugar over peaches.
Melt margarine slightly, then mix it into the cream cheese, vanilla and remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Beat in the egg and then the Bisquick.
Scoop mixture on top of the peaches and spread evenly. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until golden.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except whipping cream and vanilla in a large mixing bowl and beat on high for 15 minutes or more.
Whip cream and vanilla together and then fold into strawberry mixture. Pile this into the baked pie shell.
Freeze uncovered.
This is best if done several days in advance.
Do not let stand out of freezer any time before serving.

title: goody cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, melted margarine and chopped pecans together and press in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over chocolate layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and water in a medium saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute, then cool to lukewarm.
Combine all other ingredients in medium mixing bowl; pour warm liquid over cabbage mixture.
Stir thoroughly; store in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: peanut butter cup cupcakes
directions: Put 1 teaspoon of dough in tin and then press a peanut butter cup into the center.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 9 to 13 minutes according to package.
Let cool in pan about 20 to 30 minutes, then remove.
My nonstick mini cupcake tin says bake at 325°, so that's what I do.

title: cream cheese candy
directions: Melt cream cheese in a double boiler.
Mix in sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Drop immediately by teaspoonful onto a large sheet of wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop and mix vegetables with salt; let stand overnight. Drain.
Mix sugar, seasoning and vinegar; boil 1 minute.
Add vegetables; heat to boiling.
Pack into hot jars and seal at once.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Coat 9 X 13 inch pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar substitute, baking soda, baking powder, spices and salt.
Mix well with mixer on low setting.
Add oil and egg substitute; continue to mix on low setting.
Stir in carrots, walnuts and pineapple.
Pour into pan. Bake 25-30 minutes, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool; remove from pan and slice.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over bread cubes.
Toss lightly.
Stuff turkey or put in large pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Will stuff a large turkey.)

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Cut or slice vegetables in small pieces.
Combine meat & vegetables in large casserole.
Mix tapioca & V-8 juice and pour over meat & vegetables.
Sprinkle brown sugar & salt over top. Cover & bake 5 hrs. at 250°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well. Bake at 350° for 45 min. in greased pan. Using loaf pans or layer pans.

title: mary d's praline grahams
directions: Spread crackers on cookie sheet after breaking them in half. Melt margarine, butter and sugar in saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

Spread over crackers. Scatter pecans on top. Bake for 10 minutes at 300°. Let bubbles settle, then immediately remove to cooling rack. If you leave them for more than a minute, they're real hard to get out.

title: rock cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Add enough sweet milk to make a stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: tuna curry sandwich
directions: In medium bowl combine tuna, onions, mayonnaise, mustard and curry powder.
Fold in the banana.
Spread the mixture on 2 slices of the bread.
Top with the cucumber and the remaining bread.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Combine everything, except 1/2 can of the noodles, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix lightly and sprinkle with remaining noodles.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Do not salt. Cook chicken night before so it will be cooled for deboning the next day.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with fruit.

title: zucchini dressing
directions: Mix together; bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add bananas, eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture and stir thoroughly.
Add walnuts and mix well.
Turn into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake until tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on rack before slicing.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and oil well.
Add 1/2 cup of flour to the cream mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add salt.
Add alternately flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring and orange juice last.
Put into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 24 servings.
Freezes well.

title: open face peach pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat evenly on bottom and sides of 10-inch pie plate.
Brush bottom with beaten egg white.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Add both of above mixtures together.
Bake at 375° for 45-60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar into cornmeal in large bowl; mix well. Mix eggs, corn, milk, cracklings and shortening in bowl. Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened. Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until corn bread tests done.

title: love cake for mother's day
directions: Mix thoroughly and add 1 tablespoon smiles, 1 tablespoon hugs, 1 tablespoon kisses, 1 tablespoon surprises and 1 tablespoon laughter.
Mothers love this, so have plenty on hand and serve daily.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together and melt the brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove and add soda.
Put popcorn in a paper bag.
Pour mixture over top and shake well.
Put bag in microwave and cook on High for 1 minute.
Take out and shake. Repeat 2 times.
Turn out on waxed paper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in airtight container; store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Keeps 4 to 5 days.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with sugar and pretzels.
Spread in bottom of baking dish and bake at 350°
for 7 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add drained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
(After baking, mixture may be hard so break it up.)

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Either thaw or cook broccoli to separate it, then mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered casserole and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground meat, onion, celery and bell pepper until browned and crumbly.
Add salt and pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning, then add brown sugar, tomato sauce, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Cover and let simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach and broccoli enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in oil in 10-inch skillet until tender.
Add spinach; cook and stir until moisture evaporates.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup shredded cheese, Ricotta cheese, broccoli, 1/3 cup picante sauce, cumin and garlic salt.
Spoon 1/3 cup spinach mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining 2/3 cup picante sauce evenly over enchiladas.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining shredded cheese; top with lettuce and radishes. Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil; turn heat down and simmer.
Let mixture simmer for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Keeps in refrigerator for several months.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook rotini until done.
In baking dish, combine all ingredients.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese melts.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine pineapple and gelatin in saucepan and heat until gelatin melts, DO NOT BOIL. Cool slightly, add buttermilk and whipped topping. Combine well. Add nuts. Pour into a 9x13 pan. Chill until firm.

title: salmon pot pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add flour.
Add evaporated milk, stirring until thick.
Add cheese, salmon and seasonings. Add peas.
Place mixture into casserole.
Top with biscuits (uncooked).
Bake at 425° until biscuits are brown.
Serve hot.

title: oven french toast
directions: Place the 6 slices of bread in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Combine the milk, sugar, vanilla and eggs, and mix well.
Pour over the bread and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, combine the brown sugar, margarine, flour and cinnamon, and sprinkle over the bread.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve with chokecherry syrup, or sliced fruit of your choice.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes as usual in salted water and drain.
Whip until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
May be used anytime within 2 weeks.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Knead thoroughly. Place in square baking pan.
Let set until firm; cut into squares and enjoy.

title: pistachio salad(good st. patrick's day dessert)
directions: Mix dry pudding mix into dessert topping.
Add a few drops of food coloring to the color of green you wish.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: slumber party mix
directions: Melt oleo and mix with garlic powder, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine this with all other ingredients in large pan or roaster.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Add salt.
Add egg, vinegar and water, enough to make a dough.
Knead slightly.
Flour and roll out.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use Bundt pan.

title: white wine sauce
directions: Melt butter in small pan; blend in salt and flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolk and return to hot mixture.
Bring just to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in wine.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Meanwhile in large bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add stuffing mix, chicken, broccoli, celery and 1 cup of cheese.
Spread mixture in greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: party punch
directions: Mix juices in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Float sherbet on top.
Add ice ring made with any additional juice or ice cubes.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time. Add vanilla.
Fold in crushed crackers and chopped pecans.
Pour in pie crust and spread using back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and chill.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Divide in half.
Chill half and spread with sour cream.
Add other half of mixture and chill until set.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Brown pie crust and let cool. Soften cream cheese and mix with powdered sugar.
Spread in pie crust and on sides too.
Slice strawberries and put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: tex-mex chicken fiesta
directions: Mix together soup, water, chili powder and cumin.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring.
Add all remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup each cheese.
Spoon mixture into 10 x 6-inch dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: nancy thurmond's blackberry cobbler
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Pour batter into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.

title: swedish pecans
directions: Toast nuts in slow oven (325°) until light brown.
(Do not overtoast.)
Fold sugar and salt into slightly beaten egg whites and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold nuts into mixture.
Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Spread mixture over butter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir often until there is no more butter.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Place stacked sheets of phyllo on a flat surface and cover with plastic wrap to keep from drying out.
Place one pastry sheet on work surface.
Lightly coat with nonstick cooking spray. Top with another sheet.
Cut lengthwise in 4-inch wide strips. Move strips apart.
Mound 1 heaping tablespoon filling at one end about 1-inch from corner.
Fold opposite corner at same end over filling, forming a triangle.
Continue folding your way up the strip, as you would a flag.
Repeat.
You will have 12 turnovers.

title: crustless custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and nutmeg (if used) until smooth. Add milk and salt.
Fold in coconut (if used).
Grease pie dish. It makes it's own crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes; this prevents a soggy crust.

title: speedy dill sauce
directions: Just mix in blender or shaker and serve over your favorite fish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice and both soups together in a casserole dish.
Salt and pepper chops to taste. Layer chops on top of rice, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or 1 hour and 30 minutes, ovens vary.

title: baked butternut squash soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place squash, carrots and onion in a shallow roasting pan.
Dot with butter.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of broth over vegetables and cover the pan tightly with foil.
Bake for 35 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt. Set aside.	In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Using level tablespoon for each, shape into 5 dozen balls.
Roll each in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press an unwrapped chocolate Kiss in the center of each; bake 2 minutes longer. Remove cookies to wire rack and cool completely.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In a bag combine flour, salt and pepper; shake to mix.
Add chicken and shake to coat.
Remove chicken and save seasoned flour.
In large skillet heat 1 tablespoon oil on medium heat. Add chicken and brown on one side.
Add remaining oil and brown on other side.
Remove chicken.
Add margarine and onion; stir in reserved seasoned flour and cook 1 minute.
Add broth, lemon juice and thyme; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Return chicken; reduce heat and cover skillet.
Simmer until chicken is cooked (around 5 minutes).

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Heat tomatoes and margarine until boiling.
Mix Bisquick as directed on box for dumplings.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling tomatoes.
Sprinkle black pepper on dumplings.
Cover and cook 12 minutes on medium heat.
Do not remove cover while cooking.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except brown sugar; blend until smooth.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top and chill at least 2 hours. Stir and serve with fresh fruit.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Mix together soups and sour cream. Combine together with noodles and chicken.
Put in casserole dish. Cut up bread into cubes and brown in stick of butter.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zuppa di pesce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add parsley, tomato puree, pepper, salt and wine; stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Add the fish and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over sliced and toasted crusty bread.

title: pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pie filling mix with corn syrup.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and egg.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.

title: stuffed shells
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine onion, salt and pepper, egg, spinach, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and 1 cup of Mozzarella. Mix well.
Stuff cooked jumbo shells with this cheese mixture and place, open side down, in a large baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, vanilla and poppy seed.
Stir well. Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Add to liquid mixture.
Stir in milk.
Bake in large loaf pan, greased and floured, at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bagood's chicken divan
directions: Cook the chicken breasts, remove the bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook the broccoli until tender, cut up and place in a buttered 13 x 9 pan, place chicken pieces on top.
Drain the artichokes and place over the chicken, then sprinkle with almonds. Mix together the sour cream, soup, curry powder and wine.
Spoon over the mixture and bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 1 1/2 hours.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Blend butter, flour and brown sugar.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Add white sugar, buttermilk, baking soda, egg and vanilla.
Blend and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix reserved topping mix with Heath bars and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix everything in large bowl. Pour in 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cake mix, butter and chopped nuts. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1 package of cake mix, plus pudding in the mix, evenly over top.
Drizzle melted butter over and sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until consistency of pumpkin pie.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Serves 12.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine these and add buttermilk and soda.
Mix well.
Add cherries with a little juice, chocolate chips, dates, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and divide using 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done in center.
Wrap in foil and keep stored in refrigerator.
This is especially good at holiday time served with coffee.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups buttermilk. Cover and let stand overnight at room temperature.
In the morning, add the beaten egg and the soda mixed with the other 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Beat well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on hot, well-greased griddle.
Fry on one side and turn once only to fry on other side.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
In bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Slowly add milk and beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed; pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: pumpkin cake-bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar and oil. Mix well. Add dry ingredients; mix well. Add pumpkin and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients well and pour into casserole dish (9-inch square).
Combine brown sugar, margarine, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well until crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Spread on top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In casserole dish, melt butter and add onion and frozen broccoli.
Steam until tender.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz to mixture, then stir in rice.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Let stick of margarine soften at room temperature.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt into margarine.
Cut in until particles are fine.
Add egg and milk and stir until forms a ball.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll until 1-inch thick.
Cut with glass and bake on cookie sheet at 425° for about 20 minutes until very lightly browned.
These can be frozen unbaked until ready to bake.
Defrost slightly on cookie sheet before baking.
Delicious with strawberry jam.

title: jenny prater's hot spiced tea
directions: Bring water, cinnamon, cloves and allspice to a boil.
Add tea bags.
Steep 5 minutes, then strain.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat until sugar dissolves.

title: parmesan casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Cool milk to lukewarm. Meanwhile, sift flour, sugar and salt into bowl.
With knife or blender, cut in butter until resembles cornmeal.
Add egg, yeast and milk.
Beat well.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Use greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 40 minutes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in pie shaped wedges.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix and freeze.
Take out 2 hours before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Add chopped vegetables. Cook until almost done. Add the vinegar, sweetener, Worcestershire sauce and blend.
Add tomato sauce.
Heat and serve on buns or baked potatoes sprinkled lightly with shredded cheese.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Line pie crust with peaches, half side up.
Mix the sugar and flour; sprinkle over peaches.
Add the half and half; sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Turn back oven to 375° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except corn flakes and margarine. Put mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover top with corn flakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar and flour in saucepan. Add vinegar and beet juice.
Stir until thick, stirring constantly. Add beets, butter and salt to taste.

title: homemade suzy-q's
directions: Prepare devil's food cake mix as directed on box.
(I bake in two loaf pans.)
Set aside to cool.

title: fresh peach bread(serves 12)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Make a well and spoon in the oil.
Add peaches and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine cheese through eggs and mix well. Drain spinach and add.
Put into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and put in the refrigerator for 1 hour to set up. Form into a ball.

title: georgia peanut butter fudge cake
directions: In a medium-sized saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Set aside.
Sift sugar, flour and soda into a large mixing bowl.
Pour cocoa mixture over sifted ingredients. Mix well with a spoon.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Warm peanut butter to spreading consistency and spread on cold cake.
Cover with fudge frosting.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix oil and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add baby food to mixture and then nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make frosting.

title: low-fat dip
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender; process until smooth. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crepes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the milk.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a whisk until the mixture is thin and creamy. Spray an 8-inch round nonstick skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium to medium-high heat.
Pour in batter, spreading to edges to flatten.
Brown on both sides.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat oleo in rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) in oven until melted.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Spoon pineapple over brown sugar.
Spread evenly.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package; pour over pineapple.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto platter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line cake pan with 1/2 bag crushed Fritos.
Cover Fritos with chicken.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix soups, tomatoes and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle chopped onions across top. Layer remaining Fritos on top of onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a double boiler, melt 1 pound chocolate with butter; set aside.
In a large metal bowl, combine eggs and sugar.
Place bowl over pan of boiling water.
Using wire whisk, beat sugar and eggs until sugar dissolves and mixture is warm to touch.
With electric mixer, immediately beat mixture until triple in volume, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Fold flour and chocolate into eggs.
Pour into an 8-inch round cake pan, lined with parchment paper.
Bake exactly 15 minutes and cool.
Place in freezer for at least 24 hours.
When ready to serve, remove cake from pan and peel off paper.
Whip the cream with powdered sugar and liqueur until peaks form.
Top cake with whipping cream.
With potato peeler, form curls from remaining chocolate and pile curls on whipping cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: eggs lorraine
directions: Coat 8-inch square shallow baking pan with nonstick spray. Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Crack eggs over cheese evenly. Break egg yolks; do not stir.
Drizzle cream over eggs.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover and refrigerate now, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until eggs are set, but not hard and cheese is melted.
Add bacon and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer. Sprinkle with parsley; serve immediately.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add rice and seasonings, Cook and stir to brown rice lightly.
Add broth.
Place in 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
If desired add vegetables.
Chop 1 to 2 cups vegetables such as green peppers, cabbage, celery and small amount of onions.
Add water chestnuts if desired.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place first 5 ingredients into large saucepan or Dutch oven. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until almost tender.
Add noodles and cook about 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti-meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients well.
Shape into balls.
Brown in 1/4 cup oil and drain well.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot long enough for cheese to melt and to get hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: peanutty chewy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add butter; cut in with pastry blender or with hands until mixture is well blended, resembling coarse crumbs. Add eggs; mix well.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan, pressing firmly onto bottom of pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in top of double boiler until hot and well mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add milk, nutmeg and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together and combine with other mixture.
Add additional flour to roll out, then cut into rounds.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: microwave noodle casserole
directions: In
quart
casserole,
cook
noodles in 2 1/2 quarts boiling water; drain.
Cook beef in microwave about 4 minutes, stirring
once
or twice.
Drain excess fat. Add tomato sauce, salt
and
pepper;
cook
minutes
by
microwave.
Combine cheeses
with onion and green pepper.
In casserole layer half the noodles,
all
cheese mixture and remaining noodles, then all meat sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook by microwave 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook limas to barely tender.
Brown pepper in butter.
Mix with limas which have been drained.
Mix in celery soup gently. Place in greased casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili spaghetti
directions: Make your regular chicken salad.
Leave out the onions.
Dice a red apple with peel on.
Cut apple real fine and add to your chicken salad.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and shortening with pastry blender.
Add egg, milk and blueberries.
Blend slightly. Sprinkle muffin tops with a little granulated sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese very good, then blend in 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell and put rest of Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch casserole with Pam spray.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese and onion rings.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle cheese and onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute ground pork and squeeze between paper towels to get rid of excess fat.
Use a flat aluminum or glass dish.
Spray with Pam and add all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover with foil.
Do not stir while cooking or lift foil.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Make dough as for biscuits, using 1 cup milk.
Roll out on floured board as thin as possible.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with margarine.
Roll up and cut into 3 rolls.
Place in deep baking dish and sprinkle generously with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with plenty of margarine.
Cover with 2 cups sweet milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sprinkle with a small amount of nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until brown.
When done, cover to prevent drying out.

title: modeling clay
directions: Do not double recipe.

title: nut cake
directions: Beat together brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and oleo.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the mixture with chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a jar and shake vigorously. Set aside until ready to use.
Wash and pat dry spinach; tear into bite sized pieces and place in refrigerator to keep crisp.
Fry bacon, drain, let cool and then crumble.
Chop hard-cooked eggs. Combine bacon and eggs.
Arrange the spinach in a large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over spinach leaves and tip with crumbled bacon and chopped eggs.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour or more before serving.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and butter slowly on low heat.
Add salt and pepper. When milk is scalded, add oysters with juice and continue to simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 2.

title: fruity bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Put fruit into a pan with the juice and bring to a boil. Remove from heat, stir in bread, cinnamon and banana. Spoon into a 5 cup baking dish and pour milk over it. Sprinkle with raw sugar. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until firm. Meanwhile, prepare pudding according to instructions and when the fruited pan comes out of the oven, spoon the vanilla pudding on top. Chill in the refrigerator until firm.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Put 1 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
May also add chopped nuts.
Let set overnight.

title: chicken a la king casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Mix soup, milk and salt. Heat and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup almonds and bread crumbs.
Mix with noodles and put into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Top with crumbs and remaining almonds.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Can make casserole ahead and top with crumbs just before baking.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet until brown.
Alternate layers of Tater Tots, ground chuck and sliced onion.
Pour soup contents, along with about 1/2 can water over this mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix filling, pineapple and milk together.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts; mix well.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut or smaller. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 12 minutes at 350° (just long enough to hold dough together).
Cool a little, then roll in powdered sugar.
To coat them well, it may be necessary to roll them again when cooled.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Mix pudding according to pkg. directions.
Break cake into pieces.
In a large glass punch bowl, layer ingredients in the order listed; repeat layers.
Decorate top with pecans and cherries.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: spiked kielbasa
directions: In large skillet, combine sausage and beer.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
In small bowl, stir together other 4 ingredients. Stir into sausage.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute or until slightly thickened.

title: chunky chili dip
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in cheese spread, tomatoes and chili powder.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chinese meatball soup
directions: Cut won bok in 2-inch slices.
Combine pork and next 6 ingredients (only 1/2 salt).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Heat stock.
Gently add meatballs; simmer 20 minutes covered.
Add won bok, mushrooms and salt to taste and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: peachy-keen chicken roast
directions: In a large, flat roasting pan, place the pieces of chicken, skin side up, without letting them overlap.
In a saucepan, heat the syrup from the peaches to just below boiling point.
Add the chopped onion, soy sauce, butter or margarine and Accent.
Baste each piece of chicken generously with this mixture.
Place in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.
When the chicken is golden brown and tender enough to pierce with a fork, place the peach halves, hole side up, around the chicken.
Place a cherry in the center of each peach.
Return to the oven for an additional 8 minutes, or until the peaches are warmed through.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown and drain sausage.
Then sprinkle over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over this.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Pour mixture over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate uncovered overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Dice all beef and scallions to taste.
Mix thoroughly with cream cheese.
Shape into ball.
Wrap with plastic and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In microwave or small pan saute onion and celery in margarine until clear.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. At same time cook rice.
Mix all cooked ingredients with soup and cheese.
Add salt, pepper and Tabasco to taste.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: "fat" wanda's fast fixin chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter (do not stir).
Heat 4 1/2 to 6 minutes on High power, until butter is melted.
Add nuts and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Spread into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Makes 3 pounds of fudge.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except broth.
Pour into baking dish and top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and eggs.
Mix soda in sour milk and add to mixture.
Put salt and baking powder in flour and sift into batter.
Add bananas and nuts.
I seldom put nuts in mine, whatever you want.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: walnut sauce over pasta(low-fat)
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a blender until smooth. Toss with cooked fettucine. Garnish with walnuts.
Serves 4.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli and place in ungreased casserole dish. Beat soup and milk and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over broccoli and cheese. Bake 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust as directed on box. Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy, then add sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add milk and Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with peanuts and freeze. Make 1 day before. Keep portions small. Very rich!

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples and make 32 slices. Unroll crescent rolls (16). On each roll, place 2 slices of apple; roll up and place in a 9 x 13 pan. Melt the butter. Add sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Spoon over dumplings. Pour Mountain Dew around dumplings. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover with foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Mix together other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4.
Turn over after half of cooking time, but if you're not able to, don't worry.
Delicious anyway.
Chicken falls off bone.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix
cake
as directs on box.	In 9 x 13-inch cake pan place pecans and coconut.
Put cake mix over nuts and coconut. Mix remaining
ingredients and place on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cabbage and meatballs
directions: Boil cabbage leaves; drain and set aside. Mix hamburger and other ingredients together and roll meatballs. Wrap each in a cabbage leaf and place in a large boiler. Add 1 can tomatoes and cover with water. Cook for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: ravioli alla florentine
directions: In a wide frying pan, saute spinach in butter; add ravioli in a single layer, separating them as they thaw out; turn over once. Pour cream over and bring to boil over high heat.
Simmer for about 10 minutes or until ravioli is heated through and cooked (check one).
Fold in the Parmesan and serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix together beans, chilies and taco seasoning.
Spread in cake pan.
Blend lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth. Spread on top of bean mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of sauce mixture.
Top with lettuce, cheese, rest of taco sauce and olives. Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: freezing corn
directions: Mix together and put in large roaster.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put in freezer bags. Makes 9 pints.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and cook together the pudding and milk.
Cream for 20 minutes:
oleo and sugar.
Add to pudding mixture and pour on cake.
Spread one can pineapple pie filler on top.
Sprinkle coconut on cookie sheet and toast in oven until browned.
Sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sesame swirl biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter or magarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir sour cream and milk together.
Add all at once to dry mixture.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on well floured surface (10 to 12 times).

title: spud soup
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and set aside.
In approximately 4 cups of water, boil potatoes, carrots and onions until tender.
Meanwhile, melt butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook for about 1 minute.
Add milk all at once, blending until smooth; cook until thickens.
Add to cooked veggies (do not drain).
Add bacon.
Add more milk if needed.
Garnish soup with grated cheese.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Whisk together orange juice, chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, hot mustard and red pepper flakes in a small mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In a medium skillet heat oil.
Cook chicken until done and remove from heat.
Set aside.
Reduce heat and add celery; cook 1 minute.
Add squash, zucchini and 2 tablespoons water.	Cook until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add red peppers and cooked chicken.
Then add sauce and allow to simmer on low heat until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Serve over rice if desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and boil 5 minutes.
When meat is done, warm the sauce and dip meat down in the sauce, then put on the grill.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. To mix for a cup of tea, blend 1-2 tsp. of mixture in a cup of hot water.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter or oleo. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla (peanut butter if desired).
Beat with spoon until thick.
Spread in buttered dish and cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Delicious!!!

title: plum cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Make a nest in mixture and add next 3 ingredients.
Mix all these together.
Add pecans. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown meat and onion, stirring often to break up meat.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, fennel seed and oregano.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Split rolls; spread with garlic spread on top half of roll.
Divide meat evenly.
Place slice of cheese on each.
Wrap in aluminum foil and heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter incredibles
directions: Crush graham crackers, then combine first 4 items.
Pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over graham mixture.
Smooth out and refrigerate 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Do not allow chocolate to set firm before cutting!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with 1 whole package from box crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes; take off heat and add instant coffee.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and cool completely.
Add vodka and pour into 1/2 gallon jug, add vanilla and shake well.
Can be used immediately.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large saucepan, saute garlic in olive oil over low heat for 2 minutes. Add tomato sauce and tomatoes, pepper and oregano. Simmer gently, uncovered, while preparing other ingredients. Saute onions in remaining olive oil over low heat until onions are transparent. Add thawed spinach and toss with onions, separating and heating spinach.

title: jo's broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Cook and cube chicken.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup and lemon juice.
Spread broccoli on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add cubed chicken, then soup mixture.
Sprinkle on top Pepperidge Farm herb dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, not covered.
Bake until almost done, then add cheese so it won't be hard.

title: texas cheese dip
directions: Cook meats and drain on paper towels.
Discard grease; return meat to pan.
Add diced cheese and picante sauce.
Heat on low to melt cheese.
Stir occasionally.
Place in crock-pot to keep warm. Serve with chips.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook the spaghetti in the broth that is left over from cooking the chicken (reserve 1/2 cup broth for casserole).
Drain spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish; sprinkle the cheese on top.
Heat oven to 350° and bake casserole for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix until blended.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes. Pour batter into 10-inch greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pineapple spread
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar, vinegar and juice.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool, add mayonnaise and drained crushed pineapple.
Spread on white bread for sandwiches.

title: gladys lacy's christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Add 1/3 cup of pear juice and cubed pears.
Pour into 9 x 12 clear pyrex dish and gel.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen in water until done.
Boil celery and onions.
Boil spaghetti in broth.
May have to add water.
Add soup and mashed tomatoes.
Cook on low fire with approximately 1 can of water. Grate up cheese.
Stir cheese in liquid until it melts.
Put cheese on top and bake until it melts.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with onion, salt and pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce, brown gravy, water and green beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Top with mounds of mashed potatoes and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: oyster soup
directions: Make a roux as follows:
Melt the butter or oleo; add flour and onion, chopped fine, and 8 oysters, drained of their liquor and chopped in small bits.

Brown all, stirring constantly to avoid burning, then add the oyster liquor and an equal amount of water. Add a few stalks of chopped celery (this gives it a good flavor). Season with pepper and salt.
Let simmer slowly for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: In large bowl, soften yeast in warm water.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine and honey.
Remove from heat and add to this the beer and next three spices.
When just warm, add beer mixture to the yeast and stir in a combination of the rye flour and 1 1/2 cup flour.
Then add enough white flour to form a ball of dough and knead this on a board for about 5 minutes.
Form a nice round loaf and place in a greased 8-inch pan in a warm area to rise for 1 hour.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Great with soup meals and no hangover!!!

title: osgood pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, butter, spices, vinegar, pecans and raisins that have been put over steam to plump.
Last, fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until thick and brown.

title: cole slaw by jane
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and allow to season for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans and pack in baking dish (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and 3/4 of Cool Whip (save enough for topping).
Spread mix on cool crust.
Mix together pudding, milk and lemon juice and spread over cream mixture.
Top with Cool Whip that was saved and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate frozen bananas
directions: Peel banana and cut in half.
Insert stick.
Place on tray.
Freeze until firm (about 1 hour).
Combine chips, fudge topping, water, and microwave for 45-60 seconds.
Stir.
Remove bananas from freezer, dip in chocolate, roll in rice cereal, and refreeze.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Knead crescent roll dough together.
Fix on cookie sheet and bake 11 to 13 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread over cooled dough crust.
Cover with chopped vegetables and top with shredded Velveeta.
Nice summer party pleaser!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in large pan on stove:
sugar, milk and margarine. Bring to boil.
Turn to medium heat.
Stirring constantly, boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.

title: potluck bean bake
directions: Combine ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir to mix. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Peel and cut apples.
Put in bottom of pie plate.
In bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour, melted butter, chopped nuts and eggs.
Pour over apples. Then top with teaspoon of cinnamon. Bake for approximately 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and salt in small bowl.
Blend in shortening with pastry blender until mealy.
Sprinkle water on and toss with fork until sticks together.
Roll out 1/2 on well floured surface.
Put in pie plate and crimp edges.
(Makes 2 crusts; can freeze one.)

title: polish balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Form 1-inch balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; shape into balls.
Place in refrigerator for about 20 minutes.
Take out and roll in pecans. Let set overnight before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.
This freezes well.

title: raisin puff pie
directions: Beat on low speed all ingredients, until very fluffy.
Stir in raisins and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sanders frosting
directions: Beat egg white and salt until stiff in glass bowl.
Cream the sugar, shortening and butter; beat well.
Fold in egg white and mix well.
Blend in milk, 1/4 cup at a time.
Beat well and add vanilla.

title: breath of spring delight
directions: Bring water to a boil, add Jell-Os and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until consistency of egg whites.
Cream the cheese; add vinegar, pineapple and nuts.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Chill until congealed.

title: rubber cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with a spoon until well mixed. Pour into 13 x 9 pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Cut pineapple in half lengthwise.
Cut fruit from shells, leaving shells intact.
Cut pineapple into chunks.
In bowl, combine fruit and spoon into pineapple shells.
May be served with yogurt.

title: microwave sticky buns
directions: Measure biscuit mix into 1-quart bowl.
Stir in milk to make soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured pastry cloth.
Knead lightly several times.
Roll out in 8-inch square.
Brush with melted butter.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on dough.
Roll up.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Combine softened butter and brown sugar in 8-inch cake dish.
Spread to cover bottom. Scatter nuts over sugar mixture.
Arrange rolls in dish.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High, or until toothpick inserted is clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (175°C). In a large bowl, mix together ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs and ketchup. Season with Italian-style seasoning, oregano, basil, garlic salt, diced tomatoes and cheese. Press into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and cover loosely with foil. Bake in a preheated oven approximately 1 hour or until internal temperature reaches 160° (70°C).

title: fried fatback and milk gravy
directions: Fry fatback in black iron skillet until golden brown and all fat is cooked out of meat.
Pour off excess grease.
Brown about 3 tablespoons of flour in grease.
Add about 2 cups of milk and water.
Thicken gravy to thickness desired.
Serve with hot, homemade biscuits.
This meal is good with fried corn and sliced tomatoes.

title: nut balls(great for the holidays)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given (add pecans last).
Form dough into small balls.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes, then increase heat to 325° and bake for an additional 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.
Usually requires two rollings to coat them thoroughly.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake according to directions. Mix sour cream, sugar and 1 package of coconut in bowl; mix well. Set in refrigerator.
When cake is done, slice layers in half with thread.
Take out 1 cup of sour cream mixture and layer between all 4 layers of cake.
Place cake in refrigerator for 30 minutes or until cake is cool.
Mix remaining sour cream mixture with Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread mixture over cooled cake and sprinkle with remaining package of coconut.
Keep cake in refrigerator.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: In bowl,
cut
shortening
into flour, spices, salt and sugar. Reserve
cup for later.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased
9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice in medium size saucepan until boils. Dissolve Jell-O in hot pineapple.
Beat cream cheese in mixture until smooth.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or salad bowl.

title: mom's chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well in heavy saucepan.
