Add milk, butter and egg yolks.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and stir well.
Cook until thickened and pour into baked pie shells.

title: simple tiramisu
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large mixing bowl at high speed of an electric beater until light and fluffy. Add 1/4 cup coffee, beating just until blended. Stir in grated chocolate and 1/2 cup almonds. Set aside 1 cup whipped topping. Fold remaining whipped topping into cream cheese mixture. Brush cut sides of ladyfingers thoroughly with remaining 1/2 cup coffee. Arrange 2/3 of ladyfingers in bottom and up sides of a 2-quart bowl (such as a large mixing bowl). Spoon cream cheese mixture into center. Top with remaining 1/4 cup almonds. Cover and freeze 30 minutes. Garnish, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: bacon cocktail wieners
directions: Wrap bacon around cocktail wieners and secure with toothpick. Roll in brown sugar and bake at 350° until bacon is done, about 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Mix all together, then add topping before cooking.

title: polish lasagne
directions: Combine soups and water.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a very thin layer of soup mixture.
Then put a layer of noodles, 1/2 onion, 1/2 sauerkraut and 1/2 cheese, then noodles, hamburger, onion, sauerkraut and cheese.
Mix soups together.
Pour over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° covered, then uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and flour, using a pastry blender.
Cut butter into ingredients.
Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with ice cream.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oatmeal and buttermilk; let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs, then dry ingredients.
Fry in lightly greased skillet. Makes 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken, sausage, Taso, chopped onion, bell pepper, garlic, thyme, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper until chicken is done.
Take chicken out and debone and set aside.
Put oil in skillet and add flour and brown, stirring constantly on medium heat.
When as brown as you want, pour into pot with juice that you cooked the chicken in.
Turn to high heat. When this starts to boil, turn to medium heat and add chicken, parsley and green onions and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.
Sprinkle file (felay) over top.

title: five minute cookies
directions: Mix oats, coconut, peanut butter and vanilla.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mix over oat mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: favorite dinner rolls of rev. and mrs. w.a.e. johnson
directions: Pour warm water into large mixing bowl.
Dissolve sugar in water.
Stir in yeast until it melts.
Combine solid shortening and hot mashed potatoes.
Mix until soft and room temperature. Beat eggs until room temperature.
Add to mixture.
Stir in flour 1 cup at a time.
Cover bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Dough should double.
Form into desired shape.
Baste with melted butter.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water; add cold water. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Slice strawberries; reserve a few for garnish, if desired.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Stir whipped topping into gelatin until well blended.
Gently stir in strawberries and cake cubes.
Spoon into a 10-inch tube pan or a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Unmold or cut into squares; garnish with additional whipped topping and strawberries.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly the condensed milk and egg yolks.
Add lemon juice last and mix well.
Pour into pie crust.

title: deep chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt candy bars and syrup together in top of double boiler.
Add vanilla.
Stir and cool.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in chocolate mixture; beat.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to the first mixture. Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican dish
directions: Crush 1/2 cup chips; place in bottom of large casserole dish. Add corn (drained).
Remove tamales from sauce.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Add chili beans.
Layer with another 1/2 cup crushed chips.
Pour sauce from tamales over chips and cover with cheese. Put in microwave oven until cheese melts.
(If not hot enough, dust with chili powder.)

title: zippy onion potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1-inch cubes, leaving skins on potatoes.
Put potatoes in large Ziploc bag with onion soup mix and oil; shake to coat.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and Crisco thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat all the ingredients 5 minutes.
Add orange flavoring and vanilla.
(I also add a little food coloring, a few drops of yellow and red make orange.)

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put one pound grated cheese on top.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: In saucepan, bring broth to boil.
Add carrots; simmer 2 minutes; cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 6 hours or more.
Stir occasionally.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve oleo, sugar and salt in scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to milk mixture.
Mix in eggs and cardamon.
Gradually add about 7 cups flour until dough does not stick to fingers (but softer than bread dough).
Place onto a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double.
Divide dough into two pieces and roll each into a rectangle about 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts or raisins.
Roll as for jelly roll and seal edges.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place into 9 x 12-inch greased pan (12 rolls to a pan).
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool.
Frost with thin powdered sugar frosting.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn seed.
Boil the margarine, brown sugar and Karo for 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle the baking soda in.
Pour over popcorn and toss to mix.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.
Stir and bake another 10 minutes.

title: mincemeat bars
directions: Mix
dry ingredients together and add 1/2 cup vegetable oil. Stir
until crumbly.
Keep out 1 cup and press remainder in 9
x 13	x
2-inch
pan.
Spread
mincemeat
over this and sprinkle top with
reserved
mixture
and 1 cup chopped nuts. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky road dessert pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a pie plate and dust with sugar. Reserve 1 2/3 cups cake mix; keep it dry.
Beat remaining cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Spread in a pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into a baking dish in small pieces.
In bowl mix 1 cup sugar, milk, vanilla, egg yolks and butter and pour over bread in 10 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Remove and make meringue.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Cover pudding with meringue and rebake for 2 to 4 minutes, until meringue is golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: sausage-wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain very well. Add cooked rice and other ingredients. Mix well. Just heat until hot and serve.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Beat
eggs, sugar, shortening, molasses and sour cream, then add
salt, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and baking powder. Mix well, then begin adding flour.
Let stand overnight.
Drop by teaspoonfuls or roll out.
Bake at 375°.

title: mom's tamale pie
directions: Combine ground beef, onions, green pepper and oil.
Brown in a large skillet or pan.
Then add tomatoes and corn.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper.

title: hot egg nog
directions: Place milk in 2-quart casserole.
Heat on full power for 9 to 11 minutes or until heated through and temperature of 190°F is reached.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Beat egg yolks with sugar and spices in small bowl.
Stir one cup of hot milk into egg mixture, then gradually blend all of egg mixture into milk.
Heat on full power for 2 or 3 1/2 minutes or until warmed.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Stir in vanilla.

title: quick banana muffins(banana-nut muffins)
directions: Combine biscuit mix and brown sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients until the batter is moistened; do not overbeat. Grease bottoms of 12 muffin cups.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: indian rice country
directions: Mix everything, including juices.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Take out and stir.
If dry, add water.
Place back in oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not overmix).
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (if pan is glass, bake at 325°).
Do not overbake.

title: fireside fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to soft ball stage, 238°, stirring occasionally.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; stir to blend.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in pot on low heat.
Add cocoa; stir well.
Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs and vanilla flavoring; mix well.
Add pecans; stir.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until side is set and middle is not hard.
Cool; serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 1 pie.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel apples and fill 3 quart crock-pot full.
Cook 12 hours on low.
Add sugar, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Turn on high and cook for 4 more hours.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and baking soda together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat in mixer at medium speed.
Dough will be stiff. Add pineapple.
Mix with spoon.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 25 minutes before removing.
Powder with confectioners sugar or you may apply your favorite icing.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and salt; let set overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Add cider vinegar, celery seed, sugar, turmeric, cornstarch, mustard seed and pimento.
Mix and cook 30 minutes. Bottle and seal.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan or baking dish.
Set oven at 350°.
Cream sugar, egg and butter together until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Gradually beat into butter mixture.
Add vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour into cake pan or dish.
Bake 50 minutes.
Test.
Frosting or drizzled frosting on top after cooling is optional.

title: party punch
directions: Beat orange juice, sherbet and ice cream with rotary beater until well mixed.
Add ginger ale.
Stir well.
Serves 30.

title: cherry cheese brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Pour in oblong baking dish and bake for 20 minutes.
While brownies are baking, mix together cream cheese, condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture over brownies and continue baking for 15 minutes. Allow to cool and pour cherry pie filling over cheese mixture.
Cut into bars.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out, cut and put on top of stew, leaving cover on until dumplings are cooked, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "lime-pineapple congealed salad"
directions: Mix water and jello; heat almost to boiling point.
Add pineapple and boil 1/2 minute.
Remove from heat and let cool. Add sour cream and nuts.
May add chopped maraschino cherries for color.
Pour into a greased mold.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt olive oil and butter in kettle.
Mix in flour until smooth.
Saute onions until soft (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Add broth, salt and pepper; simmer 30 minutes.
Add red wine and simmer 5 more minutes.
Spray soup bowls with Pam and fill with hot soup.
Place toasted bread on top and cover with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese is melted.

title: parmesan and parsley chicken
directions: Dip chicken into milk and egg, then dry mixture.
Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour.
(Check after one hour.)

title: easy chicken pie
directions: For easy preparation, saute or microwave boneless chicken. Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in prepared dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in a small bowl; pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine Recip-Ease baking mix, milk and butter in a separate bowl; stir until smooth.
Pour flour mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter the potatoes.
Cover potatoes with water and bring to a boil.
Drain potatoes, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Put a layer of potatoes in baking dish. Sprinkle on part of the sugar and dot with margarine.
Repeat this until all ingredients are used.
Slice the orange and lemon in thin slices.
Pour reserved liquid over all.
Cover and bake until syrupy.
Uncover and bake until lightly browned.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Spoon into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then on rack.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Add pineapple, butter, crumbled bread and lemon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: easy cold oven popovers
directions: Generously grease a muffin tin or Pyrex cups.
Set in cold part of refrigerator while preparing batter.
Break eggs into bowl; add milk, flour and salt.
Mix well with wire whisk or spoon, disregarding the lumps.
Fill cold greased cups until 3/4 full. Pyrex cups about 1/2 full.
Put in cold oven; set the controls at 450° now, not until turn on oven heat.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not peek.
The secret is starting with a cold oven. The popovers should be eaten immediately but if you must hold them, pierce each one.
Keep warm.
Try these fast and easy one bowl popovers that really pop.

title: chili
directions: Place meat, onion and garlic in large, heavy frypan or Dutch oven.
Cook until light-colored.
Add oregano, comino seed, chili powder, tomatoes, hot pepper sauce, salt and hot water.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.
Skim off fat during cooking.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Stir all together.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 X 13 inch pan at 350° for 35-40 minutes, or until lightly brown, then let cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: soup and rice
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased dish.
Put in oven, uncovered, at 350°.
After margarine has melted, stir well.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Measure liquids and add enough water to make 1 cup. Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in drained blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart flat pan or dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: sweet chow chow
directions: Combine in a large kettle and boil until cabbage is tender. Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: homemade deodorant
directions: Dissolve aluminum chloride in water.
Bottle and use when necessary.
Apply with a small swab of cotton.
Bathe the underarm before applying a small amount of the deodorant and let dry.
(May be left on overnight.)
Before dressing, bathe underarm and dust with powder.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add salt.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Then squeeze out excess juice.
If desired, use chopped celery, peppers or carrots.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the baking soda and nuts.
Beat down and pour over the popcorn in a large mixing pan.
Stir until all corn is coated.
Place corn on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour in a 200° oven.
Cool on pan, then break into pieces.

title: macaroni, ground meat and cheese casserole
directions: *Can add salt, pepper, garlic salt, rosemary, oregano and other seasonings to suit your taste.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Sift together. Cream the oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Start with flour and milk and end with flour.
Mix well and put in tube cake pan. Cook at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: karen's green bean casserole
directions: Mix grean beans, Cheese Whiz, about 1/3 the can of French onions, and mushroom soup together.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 13 casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbles.
Put remainder of French onions on top and return to oven until French onions are toasted but not burnt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
In a large bowl, mix all.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually. Mix in thoroughly the pecans, dates and cherries.
Drop by teaspoon into crushed corn flakes, coating all around.
Press 1/4 of a cherry on top and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: cabbage and piggies
directions: Trim and cut the cabbage into shreds.
Wash well.
Bring a large pan of water to a boil and throw in the cabbage, salt, pepper and allspice.
Cook about 10 minutes or until done.
While it is cooking, fry the bacon in the butter in a hot frying pan. After the cabbage is cooked, drain water and place it in a mound in a warm deep dish.
Remove bacon from the hot fat.
Pour the hot fat over the top of the cabbage.
Crumble bacon over the top of the cabbage.
Serve large helpings.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased pan at 400° for 1/2 hour (30 minutes).
I use my 9-inch Pyrex pie pan.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Mix all ingredients together until creamy. Spray skillet with Pam.
Get skillet hot.
Turn down to medium-high.
Pour to size and cook.

title: fish
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over fish fillets in small casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then broil for 2 minutes.

title: weight watchers dessert
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple, yogurt and dry pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Also you can substitute pineapple pudding or pistachio pudding mix.

title: citric punch
directions: Pour boiling water over acid to dissolve.
Add sugar, cold water and juice.
Freeze to mush or frappe stage.
Color if you wish.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breast in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Place rice, vegetables and 1 can of fried onions around and under chicken.
When 20 minutes is up, mix chicken broth and Italian seasoning; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Chill for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips with 1 stick of butter in microwave.
Pour over peanut butter mixture.
Smooth with spatula.
Refrigerate 20 minutes and cut into 1-inch squares. Refrigerate an additional 20 minutes before serving.

title: new orleans chili
directions: In large saucepan, combine all but beans.
Cover, simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in drained kidney beans.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes. Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: railroad dish
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook chopped bacon, drain.
In large pan, pour undiluted tomato soup.
Add macaroni, heat thoroughly. Pour grated cheese in and continue heating.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: big sister's italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until smooth. Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: hot picante sauce
directions: Grind
tomatoes, onions and jalapenos.	Pour over salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook until desired thickness.
Pour into scalded jars
and seal.
Process in hot water bath.
Makes 14 pints.

title: liver pudding
directions: Cook all ingredients, except corn meal, until tender.
Let cool in liquid.
Take out liver and meat; grind in food mill. Reheat broth to boiling.
Stir in ground meat.
Add enough corn meal to boiling mixture, stirring constantly to hold firmly together.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add sage to desired taste.
Pour into pans to cool.
When ready to use, slice, roll in flour and fry in oil until brown.
(Keep some of broth to make liver mush.)

title: speedy quiche
directions: Saute Spam, onions, and green pepper in oil and put in pie pan.
Put cheese on top of Spam.
Mix milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper and put over Spam.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: bird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or less.

title: stuffed haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse haddock fillet; pat dry.
Make a slice down fillet for stuffing.
Microwave spinach to defrost. Squeeze out excess water.
Brown garlic and butter in saucepan. Add spinach and cream cheese; mix well.
Place haddock fillet in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Squeeze lemon over fillet.
Spoon spinach mixture over fillet.
Bake in a preheated oven 20 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Garnish with fresh parsley and lemon.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
This can be served in hollowed-out bread or served as a dip for chips.

title: donna's chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Salt and pepper chicken breasts. Layer in pan the chicken and cheese; seal with soup. Mix the stuffing and margarine; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (cover first hour).

title: granny purdon's baked pepper
directions: Mash
peeled tomatoes; add bread and mix well.	Mixture should be	moist
but
not real juicy.
Add some more bread if needed. Pour
into	a
greased baking dish.
Mash into a thin layer.
Cut pepper
up	over
the
top.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on
medium for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice
gradually.
Mix next 5 ingredients; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Line
pan
with
wax
paper.
Pour batter in pan; bake for 15 minutes.
(Don't overbake.)
Invert on towel; sprinkle with
powdered sugar.
Roll cake and towel together; cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix; spread on cake, reroll and refrigerate.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; blend at medium speed for 15 seconds or until smooth.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: punch
directions: Mix, adding ginger ale last.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat until fluffy.
Add milk slowly while beating.
Add lemon juice and vanilla and beat.
Pour filling into crust.
Chill several hours and then top with cherries.

title: black midnight devil's food cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add alternately with the hot coffee until everything is mixed in (mix as little as possible).
Batter will be runny.
Grease a flat 9 x 13-inch pan and flour with cocoa.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan on rack, then turn out on rack to finish cooling.
Top with 7-Minute Icing and coconut (your favorite chocolate icing is great, as well).

title: russian tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in airtight container.
Yield: 3 3/4 c.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook rice until light brown.
Fry hamburger in fat in separate skillet.
Add onion, garlic, hot and sweet pepper, salt, tomatoes and chili powder.
Allow mixture to cook about 3 minutes.
Blend in browned rice.
Simmer slowly in skillet on top of range until done.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together in a bowl; refrigerate overnight.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together. Add sugar and egg mixture. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's. Bake on ungreased sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's. Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies. Cool.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2-quart casserole 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato mallow
directions: Cook potatoes and heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sour cream, egg yolk, salt and mace.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole and top with marshmallows.
Bake for 30 minutes until marshmallows are puffed and golden brown.

title: roasted garlic(a sweet and nutty side dish)
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass bowl with tight cover of microwave plastic wrap.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes (or longer if bulbs are large).
Remove from oven; let stand covered for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water. Blend in cranberries. Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add chopped onion, chopped bell pepper and chopped celery.
Stir in soup and tomato sauce.
Add Worcestershire sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add macaroni (precooked and drained). Pour into a casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Beat shortening until creamy in mixing bowl.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add bananas and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with banana mixture (a small amount at a time) mixing after each addition only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Turn into a greased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches) and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread is done. Makes 1 loaf.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with rhubarb.
Sprinkle with dry jello and then sugar.
Pour cream or half and half over. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Add to White Sauce. Put in casserole and mix together.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Remove shells from boiled eggs and place in a large jar with a tight fitting lid.
Pour water vinegar mixture over eggs to cover.
Cover tightly and allow to marinate for at least 2 days before serving.

title: albert dilled carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in large saucepan of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Rinse under cold running water to cool; drain.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Slice off top of cake loaf.
Scoop out center and fill with pie filling.
Replace top.
Ice the entire cake with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until serving time.
Slice to serve.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Simmer the chicken in 2 quarts of water.
Cook at medium heat until tender and done (about 30 minutes).
Remove and debone chicken.
Skim fat from liquid and set aside.
Cook oil and flour in a skillet until it turns a dark golden brown.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper; cook for 5 minutes.
Add to broth with all other ingredients, except seasoning.
Cook until rice is done. More water may be needed; add as desired.
Finish with seasonings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until done.
Drain well.
Heat other ingredients.
Add to carrots.
Marinate 2 to 4 hours.

title: caramel apples
directions: Cook slowly.
Watch for scorching until 230° or very stiff ball forms in cold water.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar and milk.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage, 234° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut when firm.

title: stars and stripes cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool. Spread Cool Whip over cooled cake.
Using blueberries, make a squared area in the upper left corner to make the "stars."
Using strawberries, make rows across length of cake to form the "stripes", being sure to leave Cool Whip showing between each row. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Blend salt, sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat milk, vanilla, margarine and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake in pie shell at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until done.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Spread on shells and roll. Wrap tightly in wrap.
Refrigerate overnight or 4 to 6 hours. Then slice in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Dip in salsa.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Put in loaf pans and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves (9 x 5 x 2-inch).

title: deli cole slaw
directions: In a saucepan, combine vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt; bring to a boil.
Stir in sugar.

title: a.1. stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers (cleaned out) about 15 minutes.
Fry onion and hamburger and cook rice.
Mix hamburger, rice, steak sauce, corn and tomato sauce.
Stuff into peppers and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salad of gold
directions: Put jello and hot water into blender, cover and process at beat until dissolved.
Remove feeder cap and add syrup, vinegar and milk.
Increase speed to liquify and add cream cheese.
When mixture is smooth, stop blender and add carrot juice.
Replace cover and process 1 cycle to liquify.
Pour into a 2-quart mold and chill until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: double cherry jello salad
directions: Chill jello until almost set.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve.

title: qualls cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add alternately milk and flour.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add flavorings. Add baking powder last.
Bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing, in large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of dressing; toss to coat.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Add remaining dressing and toss salad just before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni	until
tender.	Saute
onion
and
bell pepper in
1/4 cup melted butter.
Drain.
Brown ground beef. Mix all ingredients (except cheese) together.
Put in buttered casserole dish (1 large or 2 medium).

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Make broccoli as directed on package.
Make stuffing as directed in another pan.
Put broccoli, stuffing and cheese together.
Put in crock-pot on low for 1 hour or until ready to eat.
(May be baked in regular oven for 1/2 hour.)
Can put Durkee onions on top before you bake it.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix all together except strawberries.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May serve topped with strawberries.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain hamburg.
Break up in small pieces toss with the rest of ingredients add dressing.
Add crushed doritos at the last minute and toss again.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 minutes. Cool. Mix fruit juices. Freeze. Set out 30 minutes before serving. Add equal parts 7-Up.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a foil-lined cookie sheet with saltine crackers. Put 1 cup butter and 1 cup sugar in a medium sauce pan and heat, bring to a boil for 3 minutes. Spread evenly over the
crackers and place in a 400 degree oven for 5 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets; save liquid.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add vinegar, liquid from beets, butter, salt and paprika.
Cook in saucepan until mixture thickens.
Add beets and cook 5 minutes longer on low heat.

title: mom's salad
directions: Mix oil, balsamic vinegar, pesto and sugar together to make the dressing.

title: hot crabmeat puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Bring water and margarine to a boil. Add flour and salt. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball. Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth. Drop teaspoonfuls of batter onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes and remove from baking sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare 1 package Stove Top stuffing as directed on package. Prepare 1 package frozen broccoli as directed.
Mix both of these with mushroom soup.
Pour 1/2 in baking dish; cover with Velveeta cheese.
Pour in remaining half of mixture and dot with more cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: mom's russian fluff hot dish
directions: Put in a baking dish.
Add bacon strips on the top and bake 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve over low heat; then cool.
Beat cream cheese and remaining ingredients.
Blend in gelatin and chill.

title: oriental noodle soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except chicken; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Makes about 5 (1-cup) servings.

title: watcha call it cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg and spread in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: almond joy
directions: Bring Karo to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in coconut. Add flavoring.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let set 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
With wet hands, shape into bars.
Let dry overnight.
Top with almonds.
Coat with melted chocolate.

title: moon pie cake
directions: Boil water and margarine. Remove from heat and add flour, stirring until soft ball forms. Let cool about 10 minutes. Add the eggs, one at a time. Stir until consistency of peanut butter. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°. (Do not break bubbles in crust.) Let crust cool.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in large pan in 350°
oven.
Crush vanilla wafers on bottom of same pan.
Sprinkle coconut over vanilla wafers.
Put chocolate chips over coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Mix all together and bake for 45-55 minutes at 350°.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 12 minutes on high speed. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour without opening door.
Do not preheat oven!!

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni and drain, put in a casserole dish.
Mix sauce, mix flour, butter, cheese and milk and cook until it starts to get thick.
Pour over macaroni and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half and line the bottom of pan with cream side up.
Drain pineapple and spread on top of Twinkies.
Mix the box of instant pudding as directed on box and spread on top of the pineapple.
Slice the bananas and place on top of the pudding. Ice with Cool Whip and decorate with pecans on top.
(Twins are the same as Twinkies and cheaper.)

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except about 1/3 of the noodles.
Put in a casserole dish.
Place rest of noodles on top. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Cook rice and salt in water until tender; drain.
Add sugar, marshmallows and pineapple.
Let stand until cool.
Add whipped cream.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Mix shortening, salt, vanilla and 1/3 sugar.
Add milk and remaining sugar alternately until creamy.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Use just enough grease so they won't stick.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs and add with crushed vanilla wafers, pecans, coconut, vanilla and milk.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Combine pork and beans, onion and brown sugar in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place pork chops over beans.
Pour barbecue sauce over chops.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters in their liquor; add butter, seasonings and when edges of oysters begin to curl, add milk.
Bring just to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; cut butter into 6 pieces. Place in heated soup bowls.
Pour over soup and sprinkle with more pepper.
A few chopped mushrooms may be added if desired.

title: dessert delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13 inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next three ingredients and spread over cooled Pretzels.
Mix boiling water and Jello together until Jello is dissolved, pour in frozen strawberries and let thicken slightly then pour over top of dish.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well. Add flour sifted with salt, soda, and spices.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
This dough is soft, and must be thoroughly chilled to shape (overnight works well).
Form into small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.

title: julie's microwave popcorn sensation
directions: Put popped
popcorn
in a large bowl.
Prepare a cookie sheet or	cardboard.
(I	cover
with
aluminum foil and spray with a very small amount of Pam.)

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Lay small ball of dough on cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of a glass in water, then press glass bottom on dough to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into chilled, baked pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion with enough water to cover, until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven coated with nonstick vegetable spray until soft and light golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley and stir.
Simmer about 20 minutes until chicken is cooked and potatoes and carrots are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Sprinkle each serving with minced parsley, if desired.
Freeze remaining soup in an airtight container for future meals.
Reheat in microwave or on stove in a saucepan.
Makes 4 servings of 1 1/2 cups each.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add 1 1/4 cups sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Add sour cream, mixing until blended.

title: holiday scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of vegetables and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk and pour over vegetables.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: dried fruit balls
directions: In a blender or food processor, grind the apricots, raisins, prunes and dates.
Add coconut, nuts, orange peel and orange juice; mix well.
Form into balls; roll in finely chopped nuts. Makes 4 dozen balls.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Form pizza crust using sugar cookie dough in pan.
Bake as directed and cool.
Cream softened cream cheese with sugar. After those two are creamed, spread over cooled crust.
Spread blueberry pie filling on.
Drain cans of fruit and arrange on top of pizza in an attractive design.

title: granola(cuisinart)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 (9 x 13-inch) baking pans or large roasting pan.
Place oil, honey, water, salt, vanilla, brown sugar and cinnamon in Vita-Mix or blender container. Clamp action dome in place.
Turn speed control to high.
Lift red impact lever up to on position and run machine until steaming, about 3 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Chill 1 day before serving.

title: marinated potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and French dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, mix in eggs, celery and mayonnaise.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix and spread in buttered 8-inch (or oblong) pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, blending well after each addition. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Add last, 5 unbeaten egg whites.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: kenny's kool chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into water and coat with Shake 'n Bake mix. Place in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until no longer pink inside.
Coat chicken pieces with barbecue sauce.
Place pieces on a microwave-safe plate and cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 2 minutes or until hot.
Serve with a towel or paper napkin "to wipe off the sauce if your face gets dirty" says Kenny.

title: crisp bacon slices
directions: Place 2 layers of paper towels in glass dish.
Place bacon on top of towels.
Cover bacon with another towel.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes 45 seconds to 3 1/2 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add with milk to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 80 minutes.

title: baked trout or bass fillets
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Mix in lemon juice.
Dip fish in butter mixture and lay in single layer in pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Bake about 10 minutes in a hot oven basting several times.
Finish by putting pan under broiler until fish browns slightly but is not too dry, about 5 minutes.

title: cookies made of cake mix
directions: You may add chocolate chips or coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: bean pickles with dill
directions: Snip, wash and boil beans in salt water until tender.
Put a large head of dill at the bottom of each jar; pack in the beans. Put some dill on top.
Pour mixture made from the sugar, vinegar and water over the beans.
Seal hot.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Brown pork chops in hot fat.
Pour off fat.
Add onions, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle rice around chops and season with salt and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat until chops are tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chops.
Arrange on warm platter.
Fill in center with rice mixture.

title: vegetable dip for hot vegetables
directions: Heat soup from can; do not dilute.
Add softened cream cheese with chives.
Mix together until well blended.
Serve over cooked broccoli or cauliflower.
Can be used as a dip for fresh veggies.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple and juice and cherry pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Melt margarine in water; pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Use for veggies or as any dip.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; pat down into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over dough.

title: trash can pickle
directions: Make brine with salt and water strong enough to float an egg on top.
Wash cucumbers and put in a new trash can.
Cover the cucumbers with the brine and soak for 14 days.
Remove cucumbers and wash thoroughly in cold water.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Put back in container and cover with the alum mixed with water.
Soak overnight. Next morning, drain and rinse.
Cover with vinegar, soak 6 hours then pour off.
Use sugar, pickling spice and cucumbers in layers in the trash can.
Store covered.
Pickles will be good in 2 days and will keep.
Take out as you need them. Use 4 or 5 gallon plastic trash can with lid.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Heat to boiling point.
Pour over pickles that have been cut up and put in sterile jars with a sprig of dill.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Scrub thoroughly your coffee maker.
Rinse with hot water. Pour in a gallon of apple cider in coffee pot.
In coffee basket, put all ingredients.
Plug in and let perk as for coffee.
It stays hot as long as you wish.
You will love this drink.
Good!

title: frozen green bean casserole
directions: Place drained green beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place raw onion rings on top of beans.
Fry bacon; save drippings.
Cut bacon into 1/4 pieces and lay over onion rings.
Put almonds on top.
Add sugar and vinegar to drippings; heat until clear.
Pour over beans.
Marinate several hours or up to all night.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: make-ahead mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese. Alternate layers of meat mixture and tortillas, beginning and ending with meat mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes or cover with foil, seal securely, label and freeze.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over dates and raisins; let stand. Cream margarine; add sweetener; add egg.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt together; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, fruit, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Yields 24 cookies.
Each equals 1 bread plus 1 1/2 fat exchange.

title: sugar-free jam
directions: Bring fruit puree to boil.
Add lemon juice.
Add gelatin. Stir thoroughly and put into jars.
Must be refrigerated.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Use same flavor sherbet as Kool-Aid.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix up all ingredients.
Add milk. Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water in small bowl.
Set aside until rises.
Add to dry ingredients, along with buttermilk. Mix until blended well and kind of sticky.
Set aside in warm place.
Mixture will rise twice its bulk.
Punch down and let rise second time.
Then cut or squeeze off biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strips of beef casserole
directions: * May substitute 1 can cream of mushroom soup.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat together about 3 minutes and pour into lightly greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave chicken gumbo
directions: Place chicken in 3-quart casserole and cover.
Microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes or until meat near bone is no longer pink and juices run clear, turning over and rearranging after half the time.
Remove chicken from cooking liquid and set aside.
Skim and discard fat from chicken liquid.
Pour into 2 cup measure. Add enough water to make 2 cups, set aside.
Remove chicken from skin and bones.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Place onion in 3-quart casserole, cover and microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Blend in flour, stir in 2 cups liquid, the chicken and remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave 3 to 4 minutes or until okra slices can be stirred apart.
Microwave for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until hot, stirring once.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken, mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top. Drizzle melted butter over crumbs.
Heat in moderate oven at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Boil beans for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans.
Cover with 2 quarts water in a pot.
Bring to boiling.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Drain, leaving about 1/2 cup liquid with beans.
Add all ingredients.
Stir, cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute until tender all vegetables.
Mix with soups, rice, pepper and cream.
Fold in shrimp and crab.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and bananas to butter mixture.
Gradually add flour mixture until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown on top.
Top with Fluffy Cream Cheese Icing.

title: pasta salad
directions: Dice very fine all vegetables, chill overnight in the dressing.
Cook noodles, after cooking add to the vegetables and dressing with celery seed, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients very good and let chill until ready for use.

title: whole artichoke pickles
directions: Scrub artichokes with a wire brush, cutting off any soft spots.
Soak in strong brine for 3 days. Rub dry with a rough cloth.
Pack in sterile jars.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Fold in mandarin oranges and chill.

title: homemade dog biscuits(not for human consumption)
directions: Put yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine dry ingredients. Add chicken broth.
Mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Knead 3 minutes; mix well.
Will be stiff.
If too dry, you can add an egg or extra liquid.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Use to baste on chicken or spareribs.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bev's blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan. Take off heat and stir in brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add and fold in dry ingredients; add chopped nuts. Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan. Spread mixture and sprinkle with the chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and let cool.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients except okra and oil.
Add okra last. Heat oil in Dutch oven up to 350°.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil, and fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with more salt, if desired.
Serve hot.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 stuffing mix (including the seasoning).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread in greased cookie sheet. Divide in squares and drop pie filling in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Needs to bake longer in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: summertime salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a chilled bowl.
Makes 8 servings of 1/2 cup each.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat this mixture until fluffy and creamy.
Add evaporated milk and Dream Whip; beat well. Add strawberry Jell-O (this will turn the mix a pink color).
Add vanilla and the strawberries with the juice; beat well.
Add enough milk to finish filling a quart ice cream freezer; freeze.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour pineapple, juice and all in a container.
Add pudding mix, pecans and marshmallows together.
Mix the Cool Whip into the other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Soak bread in water and then squeeze excess water out.
Mix bread, ground beef, celery, onion, carrot and spices.
Shape into thin patties and brown in oil.
Put in large heavy pan and cover with tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Combine drained vegetables, drained pimento, chopped celery, green pepper and onions.
Stir in vinegar mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: meatballs a la king
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and salt. Shape into small meatballs.
Place in skillet and brown; drain off excess grease; add water, mushroom soup, green peppers and pimentos.
Add water, depending on thickness desired.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until peppers are done.
Serve over rice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together Veg-All, water chestnuts, cream of chicken soup, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Mix together Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Mix rhubarb, pineapple and sugar; set aside for 30 minutes. After 30 minutes, bring mixture to a boil, then turn down to simmer for 15 minutes.
Let cool 12 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add strawberry jello.
Pour into hot jars.
Delicious on toast!

title: crown jewel delight
directions: Prepare lime, orange and cherry Jell-O separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour into separate 8 x 8-inch pans.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 1/2-inch cubes.

title: quick golden stew
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine carrots, potatoes, onion and just enough water to cover.
Cook, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and ham; continue to cook 5 more minutes.
Drain water.
Stir in soup and cheese; heat through.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until soft.
Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer broccoli, chicken and cheese. Combine soup and mayonnaise; top other layers.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine. Cover soup layer.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until bread tests done.
This makes one large loaf or two small loaves.

title: olive cheese nut spread
directions: Combine
softened
cream
cheese, olives and nuts.
Add enough olive juice to make proper spreading consistency.	Add a
dash of green food color for a light green tint, or a dash of
red
for pink
tint.
Makes
enough
filling for one loaf bread.
Cut edges
from
bread, spread dressing (both sides). Put together then cut into 4 small squares or 3 fingers.

title: rose's barbecue thai chicken
directions: Prepare marinade from the peanut butter, garlic, soy sauce, ginger, catsup and honey.
Add orange juice last and whisk. Marinate chicken overnight in mixture.
Grill 2 to 5 minutes on each side, basting with marinade.
Serve garnished with orange slices and sesame seed.
Warm extra marinade and serve on the side.

title: sweet and spicy stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add pepper strips, stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add green beans,
chicken, sweet and sour sauce, red pepper flakes, pineapple and reserved juice.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until light.
Add lemon peel.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and juice, beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to batter.
Add nuts and stir until just blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, nuts and coconut.
Mix well and roll into small balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of a double boiler.
Dip each ball into chocolate mixture, using toothpicks.
Let stand on wax paper until chocolate hardens. Makes 5 dozen.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mash strawberries.
Add the juice of 1 lemon, orange juice and water; let the mixture stand 3 hours. Strain.
Sweeten to taste. Serve with ice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugars together.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, water and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add flour, then add oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Set oven at 350° and bake for about 15 minutes.

title: banana cool whip cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, making 4 layers.
Mash bananas. Sprinkle with sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Cover with Cool Whip. Put in cake keeper.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Delicious!

title: salad delight
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except the pineapple, Dream Whip and nuts.
Add the pineapple.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Fold in the Dream Whip.
Chill until firm.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: prairie eggnog pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Soak gelatin in cold water.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks.
Gradually pour milk into this mixture and return to double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, butter and vanilla. Chill.
When mixture is cool, add beaten egg whites and pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and chill for several hours. Spread with whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: cream chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Saute chopped onion and celery in chicken broth.
Add mushroom soup and a little cornstarch to thicken.
Tear chicken into small pieces; put 1 layer chicken, then crumble desired amount of crackers up on top of chicken.
Pour mushroom soup and saute onion and celery over this.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 large casseroles.

title: tangy marinade with flank steak
directions: Marinate steak for 4 hours or overnight.
Grill about 4 minutes on each side for rare.
Slice diagonally (thin).

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs with cheese and 1/4 cup oleo.
Line buttered dish with 1/2 the crumbs.
Place asparagus on top of the crumbs. Blend flour, salt, pepper, remainder of butter with milk and cook until thickened.
Add chicken and pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Melt margarine 1 minute in microwave.
Add flour, milk, salt and eggs.
Whisk only until smooth to the consistency of cream. Pour into custard cups (2/3 full) and cook on lower rack (bottom heat is required).
Do not preheat oven.
Set oven for 450° for 20 minutes, then 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown. Turn oven off.
Pierce with sharp knife.
Let stand 5 minutes in oven to dry interior.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and flatten on sheet of waxed paper about 1 inch thick.
Arrange ham and cheese slices on top of flattened meat mixture.
(May also add olives and salsa.)
Roll in jelly roll fashion and crimp edges; place in greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with fresh green salad and baked potato.

title: lemon nut cake squares
directions: Beat
cream
cheese, 2 eggs, lemon juice and flour; mix thoroughly	in a medium bowl, using a wire whisk.
Stir in the mix,
water and 2 more eggs.
Stir.
Pour over hot crust; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock lobster
directions: Mix shrimp soup and milk.
Pour over fish and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Add butter to crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over fish and return to oven for another 15 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: speedy skillet supper
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add cornstarch, brown sugar, cloves and pineapple liquid.
Blend together. Add ham slice, sweet potatoes and pineapple slices.
Cover.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 2.

title: sand cups
directions: You also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups, miniature umbrellas, candy stars, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.

title: zesty chicken
directions: You also need 1-gallon size food storage bag.

title: fagioli en salsa(green beans in tomato sauce)
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan.
Add the onions and garlic; saute until soft, but not browned, about 5 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes (a No. 2 1/2 can is 3 1/2 cups), salt, pepper, oregano and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cut the beans in halves crosswise and add them.
(Use two packages frozen, if you wish.)
Cover and simmer for about 40 minutes or until beans are tender.
Transfer to a deep serving dish.

title: chicken a la mary
directions: Make 2 cups vegetable broth by boiling the carrot, 1 onion, celery, bay leaf and salt (to taste) for 15 minutes.
Strain out the vegetables and let the broth cool.

title: chewy ginger cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening, eggs and molasses until fluffy. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Roll small (walnut size) balls of dough in sugar and bake on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until crinkled and brown. Cool on cookie racks covered with paper towels with cookies on top of paper. Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: six-weeks bread-n-butter pickles
directions: Wash whole cucumbers and pack whole in gallon (or smaller) jar.
Add 4 teaspoons salt to gallon jar and fill with vinegar. Let stand six weeks in a cool place.
Pour off all vinegar and throw vinegar away.
Slice cucumbers.

title: cheesy biscuit lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and nuts in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered
sugar.
Drop by tablespoon over cake batter.
Swirl mixture with knife in cake batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Drain juice from salmon into cup and set aside. Flake salmon. Add egg and flour.
Put baking powder into 1/4-cup salmon juice. Stir until real foamy and then pour into salmon mixture.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Brown chicken quickly in very hot oil, just enough to glaze it and firm up skin.
Remove from pan and drain.
Mix first 9 ingredients in pan and bring to simmer.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken to heated platter.
Mix the cornstarch in a bit of water and stir into sauce to thicken.
Spoon a bit of thickened sauce over each piece of chicken on platter.
Serve remaining sauce in side pitcher.

title: peach butter
directions: Put the nuts and water in the blender and run it until they are reduced to liquid paste.
Then add the other ingredients and whiz until you have a well blended butter.
Keep covered and refrigerated.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning mix in bowl, mixing well. Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great party dip!

title: frosty-dipped bananas
directions: In small heavy saucepan over very low heat, melt chocolate, stirring constantly. Do not add any liquid. Remove from heat and transfer to shallow dish. Insert wooden picks into fruit. Roll bananas into chocolate, then immediately in chopped peanuts. Place on wax paper lined cookie sheet. Freeze until firm. If not eaten the same day, wrap in moisture, vaporproof wrap and return to the freezer. Makes 8.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and butter or oleo.
Add flour, salt, orange slices, eggs, dates and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Cool in pan.

title: mary meskauskas' zesty macaroni bake
directions: In pan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, 1/2 cup water and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix sauce and macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir, then top with crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: chocolate peanut butter sticks
directions: Melt chocolate and blend with peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in wheat germ.
Press into a buttered 8-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut into bars and store in a container in the refrigerator.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Mix oil and water and stir quickly into flour.
Roll out between wax paper.

title: jean's easy fudge
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from stove.
Add 10x sugar, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into two 8-inch round cake pans. Make sure you spray pans with Pam or other cooking spray.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops in casserole in butter with garlic.
Drain.
In same casserole add uncooked rice.
Top with chops, bell peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Pour consomme over and cover.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep fryer at 375° until brown.
They are best if you cook your fish in the deep fryer first.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimiento, pepper and 1/2 cup of crumbs.
Pour into shallow casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: Wash and clean cucumbers.
Slice and pour solution of lime and water over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash with clear water.
Let cucumbers soak 3 hours in clear water.
Drain. Boil vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, boil cucumbers 35 minutes and pack in hot jars and seal.

title: zesty rice and bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil with water over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, mushrooms and green peppers; simmer, stirring often until onion is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add rice, beans, tomatoes, chili powder and hot sauce.
Cover and simmer for about 25 minutes or until rice is tender and most of liquid is absorbed.
Transfer to a 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Yields 6 (1 cup) servings.
Each contains 13 grams protein, 5 grams fat and 263 calories.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In frypan, brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce; heat until hot and bubbly. Combine cheese and sour cream. Pour hot meat mixture into ungreased 12 x 8 or 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Spread crescent rolls over top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and butter. Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: seafood pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and soup mix, then spread on round platter.
Spread seafood sauce over mixture.
Add shrimp and top with green onions.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan for 10 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion and potatoes in bacon drippings. Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; set on low heat.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat until fluffy sugar and oleo.
Put in eggs, one at a time and beat after each one, then rest of ingredients.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tabbulah salad
directions: Soften bulgur by soaking 1 hour in enough water to cover. Drain, pressing out excess water.
Combine all other ingredients and toss until well coated.
Chill.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in heavy 9-inch ovenproof skillet, preferably cast-iron, in oven while preheating to 400°.
In large bowl, mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; stir in egg and milk.
Carefully tilt skillet to coat with margarine and pour the rest into corn meal mixture.
Stir just to blend.
Pour into hot skillet; bake about 20 minutes or until golden and springy to the touch.
Cut in 8 wedges; serve hot.

title: bitter sparkler
directions: Fill glasses with ice cubes.
Shake a few drops of bitters over ice.
Top with tonic water.
Squeeze in a wedge of fresh lime and garnish with a sprig of mint.
Serves 2.

title: christmas day decoration dessert
directions: Blend together all ingredients except the cookies.
Layer in a large clay pot the pudding mixture, then cookies.
Start with cookies and end with cookies for topping.
Add plastic poinsettia flowers to "grow" in the pot and add bow.
Enjoy eating your centerpiece.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into baked pastry shell or graham cracker crumb shell.
Chill 2 hours and top with whipped cream before serving.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake by box directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix milk and caramel topping until well blended.
When cake is done and while it's still hot, poke holes in it with a fork or straw.
Pour caramel and milk mixture over cake.
Sprinkle on candy bar over the topping.
Spread Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle the other candy bar on top.
Chill.

title: men only coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as cake box says.
Cool.
Ice cake; sprinkle coconut on top.
If you want to make kids happy, put orange food coloring in coconut to decorate.
Great look for Halloween.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Boil carrots, celery and green onions in water for 5 minutes. Saute white onion in butter until translucent.
Add flour and blend well.
Boil chicken broth.
Stir into onion mixture with a wire whisk.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and vegetables (including water). Bring to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Serve immediately.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage head in half and soak in salty ice water.
When crisp, it will crunch between your teeth.
Remove cabbage and shake off excess water. Cut in half again.
Slice thinly or grate. Add your favorite dressing.

title: monkfish, prawn and clam stew
directions: Combine half the olive oil and all of the butter in a large, heavy, high-sided saute pan and place over medium heat; stir to combine.
Add the shallots, leeks and garlic and saute, stirring frequently, until the vegetables are translucent, about 3 minutes.

title: curried chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken with celery, onion and bay leaf.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Place broccoli in bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over broccoli. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy (not stiff).
Stir in sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add pecans and stir well, until pecans are completely covered.
Spread nuts on a large baking sheet and bake at 200° for 45 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
(Best if removed from oven while stirring.)	Remove from oven.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water for 5 minutes and let cool.
I use the microwave oven and just bring it to a boil.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add raisin mixture. Combine flour and all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix batter to the dry ingredients.
Blend well and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or more. Watch, don't overbake them.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.
You have to know your own oven.

title: "fresh forever" cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, butter and salad oil. Add eggs and milk. Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in vanilla, oats, coconut and nuts. Drop from a teaspoon or roll into small balls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ooey gooey yummy stuff(layered dessert)
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush nuts in food processor or blender.
Set aside 1/4 cup nuts.
Melt butter.
Combine rest of nuts, butter and flour.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and press to form crust. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let crust cool completely before going to next layer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice and onion soup mix.
Add water.
Place chicken skin up on rice.
Pour soups and milk over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; let cake cool.
Cut cake in 3 x 3-inch squares to layer in punch bowl by layers.
Layer cake in punch bowl, cover with top ingredients.

title: christmas carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Beat eggs and sugar until light; add oil.
Blend flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into egg mixture and blend well.
Add nuts, fruit and carrots.
Mix well.
Pour into pan; bake for about 1 hour.
Test to make sure it isn't wet.
If wet, continue baking until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan, cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Put in blender until well-blended.
Pour into a greased, glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick sinful snackin'
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Add Chinese noodles and peanuts. Stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in margarine until meat is brown and onion tender. Drain off fat. Add 2 tablespoons of drippings from meat to skillet.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly. Do not allow to boil. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: special dessert
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch oblong pan with vanilla wafers.
Mix remaining ingredients, except pie filling and Cool Whip.
Spread over vanilla wafers.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and chill overnight.

title: st. nikolas koekjes(dutch santa claus cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add remaining ingredients. This makes a very stiff dough. Form into a roll as for refrigerator cookies and slice when thoroughly chilled or roll on well floured board with rolling pin and cut into desired shapes. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: best  baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; arrange bacon across top of mixture. Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2- 2 hours at 325 degrees.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the half cup nutmeats with the first 3 ingredients.
Heat to boiling the milk and margarine and pour over the sugar and cocoa mixture.
Mix well and put into a greased pan.
Cool.

title: pecan torte
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
In buttered 9-inch spring-form pan or 13 x 9-inch pan, pat crumbs firmly on bottom and up sides of pan.
Chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine rice and all ingredients, except cheese, in a large casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is browned, 15 to 20 minutes (or in microwave until cheese is melted).

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers and dill in gallon jug or quart jars.
Heat vinegar, water and salt to boiling.
Put mustard seed in top of jar.
Pour solution to top of cucumbers and seal jars.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop dates into chunks, cherries and pineapple into slivers. Place fruit and nuts into a large bowl. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Cream margarine, sugar and eggs. Beat well. Mix all ingredients well. Do not use a mixer. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put squash, bell peppers and onions in a large container. Cover with salt and cracked ice.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.

title: banana split pie
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Press in dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool and add filling.

title: mary lou's christmas layered salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple and juice.
Put in tree mold.
Chill until firm.

title: ham, rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with broccoli, then ham, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: fresh tomato basil pasta sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a medium, noncorrosive skillet. Add garlic and tomatoes; cook for 5 minutes, or until tomatoes are softened.
Add vermouth and cook on high heat until slightly thickened, about 4 minutes.
Add chicken broth and continue to cook on high heat for 2 minutes longer, or until sauce thickens slightly.

title: orange 'n' nut carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat, combine marshmallows, juice and margarine. Cook and stir until marshmallows melt.
Add carrots and nuts; heat through.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole (not crushed) graham crackers.
Prepare pudding according to box directions but only use 3 cups milk. Add Cool Whip.
Make 3 layers of graham crackers with pudding in between.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin in small strips.
Brown quickly in butter to medium rare.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in remaining butter.
Add bouillon, meat and sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over green noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste. The entire recipe, with the exception of sour cream, may be prepared a day ahead and reheated with sour cream just before serving in chafing dish.

title: aunt martha's raisin drop cookies
