directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Blend thoroughly. Sift all dry ingredients except soda and add to the sugar mixture. Dissolve soda in the milk and add to mixture. Mix until well blended.
Add raisins, nuts, coconut, etc., and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° until brown or done.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package, using only one cup milk.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Spoon into pie shell.
Garnish with 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: venison roast
directions: Sear roast on both sides.
Place in large roasting pan. Sprinkle paprika, pepper, bay leaves and thyme onto roast.
Place carrots and potatoes on/around roast.
Put sliced onions onto top of roast and vegetables.
Pour mushroom soup onto roast.
Pour wine over top of everything.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups water.
Cover and roast at 350° for about 3 hours or until no red juices appear when roast is pierced.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 30 (2-inch) foil liners in muffin pans.

title: barbecue
directions: Boil meat and onion until tender; slice meat and add other ingredients.
Simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Top with cheese, if desired.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, blending well.
Stir in applesauce; mix well. (Mixture will be stiff.)
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Using small or medium-size cookie cutters, cut dough into the desired shapes. Peel away the excess dough and reroll as necessary.

title: grated zucchini
directions: Place grated zucchini in bowl; salt well and let stand 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Rinse and pat dry lightly.
Saute shallots and garlic in butter until shallots are translucent and tender. Add zucchini and mix and cook in shallow pan until zucchini is tender.
Garnish with parsley.

title: inari sushi substitute
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Make vinegar mixture by heating vinegar, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt (1/2 teaspoon) to boiling point.
Mix hot rice and hot vinegar mixture and cool in a large shallow container.
Prepare carrots, cutting them into long narrow sticks, boiling them slightly. Drain.
Cut "abura age" pockets in half to open up.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes to boil out grease.
In another pan, put in the "dashi" soup, pinch of salt, 4 tablespoons sugar, soy sauce and the boiled "abura age." Cover and boil on low heat until only a little liquid is left.
Stir in 1 tablespoon mirin. Cook 1 minute and cool.
Put the rice into the "abura age" pockets.
Serve.
Makes about 16 bags or pockets.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together Accent and cream cheese; add beef and onions. Roll into a ball and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and boil 5 pounds of potatoes until soft.
Finely chop onion and saute in butter until soft and translucent.
Grate cheese.
Mash the potatoes along with the onion mixture, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Let the potato mixture cool and then form into 1-inch balls.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for 5 minutes or until finely blended.
For best use, chill first.
Serves 1.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Drain vegetables and fold in first 5 ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Dribble melted margarine over crackers. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: german apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ingredients in order given.
Add apples and nuts last after other ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Pour into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Top with Brown Sugar Sauce.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Immediately add flour and make ball.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, with mixer. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, milk and pudding until thick.
Spread on cooled pastry.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Top with thawed Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugars, and eggs until creamy.
Add baking soda and baking powder and blend well.
Add flour and flavorings and mix. Add bananas.
Bake at 325° until center tests done, about 35 minutes.

title: cranberry freezer pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Slowly add Eagle Brand milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Fold in topping. Pour into crust.
Let chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: hershey's doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg with sprinkled taco salad seasoning packet.
Add the tomato sauce and 1/2 can water; let cool.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes, crumbled nacho chips and Cheddar cheese.
Add cooled hamburg mixture.
Toss all together.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Roll dough into small balls (makes 48).
Place dough ball into small muffin tin cup.
Press the ball to fit the cup, but not overflowing.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage.	Combine
soup, sausage and peppers in a chafing dish.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and reserve 2 Tbsp. of the juice.
Mix salmon, egg, and onion.
Add flour and baking powder to the salmon juice. Mix all together.
Form into patties and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: weight watchers polenta parmesan
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups water to full boil. Stir in polenta, Parmesan cheese, margarine and garlic powder. Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring constantly for 4 minutes. Spray 8-inch flameproof pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Pour polenta mixture into pie pan.
Preheat broiler.
Pour tomato sauce over polenta mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Broil until cheese is golden, about 2 minutes.

title: butterscotch pecan coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan. Arrange dinner rolls on nuts.
Mix dry pudding and brown sugar, then sprinkle over rolls.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Cover and let set overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Let set 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Wash grapes and snip into small clusters.
Beat egg whites stiffly.
With pastry brush, lightly paint grape clusters with egg white; allow excess to drain off.
Sprinkle grapes with gelatin or sugar.
Place on platter, covered with waxed paper.
Refrigerate until coating hardens (about 3 hours).
Makes a beautiful, edible centerpiece.

title: fettucine al burro e parmigiano
directions: In boiling salted water, add noodles gradually so boiling continues.
Meanwhile, set butter over very low heat to soften; add cream and Parmesan.
Stir until it looks smooth and creamy. Keep warm, but don't let it bubble.
Drain hot noodles; do not rinse.
Plop into warm, shallow bowl.
Pour sauce over.
Toss and twirl with fork and spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes. Place in buttered 9x13 inch pan. Crumble sausage, cook and drain; spread over bread. Mix eggs and salt and pepper; pour over
sausage and bread. Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dinner rolls out on a pan to make crust and bake as directed.
Mix the first
ingredients
and spread on the pastry.
Finely chop the
vegetables
listed and sprinkle over the mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: best in the west beans
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and cook until tender. Add the other ingredients.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine rest of ingredients except cheese. Put meat mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with sour cream mixture, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Good frozen, then baked.
Kids love this!

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown and season meat with salt, pepper and onions.
Drain and place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs for 1 minute.
Put cheese on top of meat and then pour milk over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Boil celery. Cook rice. Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain and set aside. Cook rice; set aside.
Brown onions and celery in small amount oleo.
Don't overcook.
Add undiluted soups, Cheese Whiz, broccoli and rice.
Heat and serve.
This freezes well.

title: mozzarella bake
directions: The skins of baking potatoes work best.
Wash potatoes well; bake; slice in half lengthwise and scoop them out, saving inside for mashed potatoes and leaving the skin intact.
Preheat oven to 475° and grease a baking sheet.
Slice the skins into strips lengthwise; brush with melted butter, arranging the skins on the sheet.
Bake until crisp.
Sprinkle with salt and serve as is.
Do not wrap potatoes in foil to bake.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together in a bowl the flour, sugar, eggs and butter.
Add corn and last of all milk.
Pour into casserole dish (greased) and bake at 400° until it starts to brown.
Lower heat to 300° and continue to bake until top is completely and nicely browned. Approximate cooking time:
1 hour.

title: shrimp louie dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together well; chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put 2 cups bran in large mixing bowl; pour boiling water over top.
Mix in shortening and rest of bran; add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Dough keeps in fridge for 6 weeks or more.
Add raisins or nuts before baking.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients in order as listed.
Mix sugar and Miracle Whip and spread over top of salad.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving; better if made day before.

title: carrot souffl(piccadilly cafeteria's carrot souffl)
directions: Steam or boil carrots until extra soft.
Drain well and transfer into a large mixing bowl.
While carrots are warm, add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Beat
with electric mixer until smooth.
Add flour and mix well. Add whipped eggs and beat well. Add softened margarine and beat well.
Pour mixture into a 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is a light golden brown. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar over top before serving.

title: bubble stuff
directions: Mix Dawn with water.
Stir.
Add glycerine.
Bend coat hanger into loop.
Dip loop into solution and wave in the air.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil peas for 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine ingredients and let sit overnight.

title: scripture cake
directions: This spring, my wife's sister, Birdy, came to visit.
For several years, Birdy has been on a diet, eating only food items that begin with the letter A--A chocolate cake, A rack of lamb, A side of beef, A box of donuts, etc.
After she'd spent three days with us, it was obvious we could not afford to feed her, and when she was in an eating frenzy, I was afraid to leave her alone with the dog.
On the fourth evening, I casually asked Birdy if she had yet been visited by the gopher snake that lived under the guest room floor.
The next morning at breakfast, Birdy had large, black bags under her eyes, said she'd had trouble sleeping and thought she'd go home if I'd be so kind as to carry her suitcase.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together mushroom soup, unflavored gelatin and cream cheese.
Cook over low heat until blended and gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and store in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: el gando
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add chili mix, tomatoes and a small amount of water; mix well. Simmer until reduced to desired consistency.
Prepare rice using package directions.
Heat soup and milk in saucepan until well blended, stirring frequently.
Layer ground beef mixture, rice and soup mixture in baking dish.
Add layers of corn chips and cheese. Garnish with chopped, onion, chopped olives, shredded lettuce and/or tomato wedges.

title: biscotti with anise
directions: Add dry ingredients together.
Add to this eggs, sugar, butter and anise.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool, then cut into diagonal slices.
Rebake for 15 minutes or until toasted.

title: down home stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and basil.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add corn and rice and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick chick enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 9 x 12 x 2 pan or large casserole dish. In a large bowl, combine the soups, sour cream, Ro-Tel tomatoes, green chiles and spices. Stir until well blended. Add cooked chicken pieces. Cut tortillas in quarters. Line bottom of pan with a layer of tortilla quarters (approximately 4 tortillas per layer or 16 quarters per layer). Add about 1/3 of the soup/chicken mixture and spread evenly over tortillas. Sprinkle with 1/3 of the chopped onions and grated cheese. Repeat layering twice. Additional grated cheeses may be needed to completely cover the top. Sprinkle with black olives and green onions if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Remove from oven. Let stand for 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: burger beans
directions: Fry the ground beef.
Add the sugar, salt and pepper.
Add the chopped onion and green pepper.
Let fry until the onion and pepper are soft.
Add the tomato sauce and baked beans.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: caramel candy
directions: In saucepan or double boiler, cook sugar, corn syrup, butter and 1 cup milk.
After this is well blended, add rest of milk. Mixture will turn brown while cooking.
Takes about 50 minutes until right consistency.
Pour into buttered pan and place in refrigerator until firm.

title: two bean franks
directions: In 3-quart casserole combine onion, celery and garlic; cover with lid.
Microwave on High 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; microwave on High 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir twice during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Arrange in 10-inch greased Pyrex plate.
Combine sugar, milk, 1/2 cup Bisquick, eggs and 2 tablespoons of butter in blender on high speed for 15 seconds.
Pour over apples.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add oil, garlic, lemon juice, dry mustard, Worcestershire, crushed red pepper, oregano, basil, tarragon, salt and 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Mix well and simmer over low heat until garlic is lightly blond.
Turn off heat.
Take each shrimp and dip into mixture so they are thoroughly coated. Arrange shrimp in pan.
Add wine to skillet; bring to a boil, then simmer until liquid is reduced by 1/4.
Spoon over shrimp.
Bake shrimp approximately 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve over fresh pasta. Sprinkle pasta with Parmesan cheese (angel hair, linguini and even stuffed tortellini are excellent choices).
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp and decorate with remaining parsley.
Serves 6.

title: hot tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Fill hamburger buns; top with tomato slice and cheese.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Put in tightly covered casserole and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix together soup, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion.
Put this on potatoes.
Spread corn flakes on top and drizzle melted butter on top of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water according to directions on package; drain.
Meanwhile, in heavy skillet cook ground beef until it loses its red color, break into small pieces.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft, remove any excess fat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Stir in mushrooms to spaghetti sauce.
Combine sauce and spaghetti pouring into 2 quart baking dish.
Arrange Mozzarella cheese over the top until covered.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until brown and bubbling for 1 hour.

title: roasted southern pecans(sweet and piquant)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Place the egg white in a large stainless steel bowl and whisk until frothy.
Whisk in the sugar, paprika, worcestershire, cayenne and salt.
Add the pecans and toss until completely coated.
Transfer pecans to prepared sheet and arrange in a single layer.

Place in the oven and cook, stirring every 15 minutes, until lightly colored and dried out, about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from the oven, immediately loosen the nuts with a metal spatula and set aside to cool before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: whipped cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: orange freeze pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in orange juice; add ice cream, a little at a time.
Blend and dissolve.
Chill slightly until a little thickened.
Stir in oranges and add cream.
Pour into shell. Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Remove about 15 minutes before serving.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender. Mash or beat until smooth. Add cream cheese and 1/4 cup butter. Beat until smooth. Add sour cream.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute steak, garlic, onion and bell peppers in margarine. Stir in tomatoes and beef bouillon; simmer for 20 minutes.
Blend together water, cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar.
Add to cooked meat mixture and cook, stirring until thickened, then simmer 2 more minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Toss noodles and cheese; serve the pepper steak over the noodles.

title: mexican lentils and chicken(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Soak lentils in 4 cups water overnight. Place chicken in crock-pot; add lentils with water, tomato sauce and cilantro. Cook 8 to 10 hours on low until chicken is tender. Serve with quesadillas.

title: pineapple-peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour peaches into a 9 x 13-inch pan; add tidbits.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Add margarine chunks.
Pour reserved juices over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and the strawberries until light and fluffy.
Add to this mixture the dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Fill the pans about 1/2 full.
Thaw the strawberries before using.

title: lonormi's fat-free, guilt-free pasta salad
directions: Combine pasta, vegetables and cheese in any proportion/combination you choose.
Stir gently to mix.
Pour dressing over mix; stir gently.
Refrigerate in tightly sealed bowl for at least 12 hours.

title: quick and easy pizza crust
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine water and oil; add to flour mixture. Stir until mixture forms a ball.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place the dough in a large bowl coated with cooking spray, turning to coat top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, until double in bulk.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pan lined with waxed paper or drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: strawberry pudding dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat pudding and 1 cup milk; add softened ice cream.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Mix jello and 1 cup hot water.
Add thawed berries and juice.
Pour over cake.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm (overnight).
Frost with whipped topping.

title: brian's sausage bread
directions: Follow baking directions for oven temperature. Let dough rise according to package. Brown the sausage with the onion; crumble in pan. Drain and let cool. In a large mixing bowl, combine both shredded cheeses, sausage, spices and the yolk of the egg. Mix well. Roll out bread dough flat. Pour mixture evenly on the dough. Roll, making sure that sides are tucked in. Before you are finished rolling, coat with egg white to help seal the bread. Put on a pan and coat the rest of the bread with the remaining egg white. Bake until outer crust is brown.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Mix water, egg yolk, sugar and flour together and pour over rhubarb.
Dot with butter. Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes. Crust should be golden brown and filling thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Cover pie with meringue and bake at low temperature until golden.

title: tarheel hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add milk.
Stir and add enough water to make stiff consistency.
Cook in deep fat at 375°.

title: macadamia chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg. Sift in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and Macadamia nuts.
Shape into balls, 1 inch apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake on top rack of oven for 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: three sisters stew
directions: Cook corned beef per package directions.
Drain and cool. Remove all fat and slice into chunks.
Set aside.
In large kettle, cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add water, whole canned tomatoes with liquid from the can and the cornmeal.
Stir well.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add green beans, kidney beans, tomato paste, corned beef, salt, pepper and other spices.
Let simmer 1/2 hour to 2 hours (just needs to be heated, but extra time blends the flavors).
Add corn-on-the-cob.
Simmer another 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple with cheese
directions: Drain pineapple, keeping 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Add grated cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine margarine and Ritz crackers, then sprinkle it over pineapple mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: banana pudding
directions: Chill can of Eagle Brand milk in refrigerator.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Refrigerate until good and thickened, then add Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a large bowl, put a layer of banana wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layers. Chill.

title: scampi oreganato
directions: Blend seasonings with melted butter. Brush over shrimp (leave shells on). Broil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve over Rice Pilaf.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Store in a sealed container.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons for each cup of hot water. Yields 3 cups of Mocha Mix.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 5 hours, covered, at 250°. Do not uncover while cooking.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix together sugars, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Beat egg yolk slightly with fork and add along with cream.
Beat egg whites stiffly and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt in double boiler or microwave marshmallows.
Mix in cream cheese.
Add lemon juice and whip.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Just before serving, top with fresh fruit.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Stir-fry noodles in oil until golden brown.
Remove remaining oil.
Add rice and chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut butter into pats and place on top.
Cover pan with tight fitting lid.
Bring to boil.
Turn heat down to simmer.
Let cook until all broth is absorbed and rice is done.

title: potatoes and carrots
directions: Chop onions into large pieces and saute in oil with minced garlic.
Peel and cut carrots into strips.
Add to onions and saute for 10 minutes.
Peel and quarter potatoes.
Add to onions and carrots.
Add salt, turmeric and ginger; stir well.
Add water and cook until carrots and potatoes are easily pierced with fork (enough water to make a sauce).
Add hot peppers and serve. (Peppers are for seasoning, but not to eat.)

title: magic blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Remove from oven.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and 1 cup sugar until well blended.
Add milk and mix until blended. Pour this mixture over butter, but do not stir.
Pour blackberries over this mixture, but do not stir.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over berries, but do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes. It should be brown when done.
Serve warm.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix stuffing and butter and press half in bottom and sides of baking dish.
Stir together soup and milk; add rest of ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread
mixture in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix and toss all above ingredients.
Add 1 cup of sour cream. Crush some potato chips in your hand and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at350°.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in layers or loaf pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll dough out onto an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, Hidden Valley mix and onion.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Use vegetables of various colors for prettiest pizza; sprinkle onto creamed mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Add sliced olives and bacon bits if desired.

title: scalloped green peas and onions
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and seasonings. Combine onions and peas.
Place in greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over vegetables; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until soft.
Put hot potatoes in a bowl and remove skins.
Add butter, brown or white sugar and 1 egg for every 2 potatoes.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in a greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
During last 10 minutes of cooking, top with marshmallows.

title: garlic batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, salt, garlic and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat 1 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir down by beating 25 strokes by hand. Spread evenly in a greased loaf pan.
Pat with a floured hand to smooth the top.
Let rise until doubled, about 40 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes, or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Brush top with melted butter; remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels; mix with 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine. Press in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for about 7 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar. Layer on top of cooled crust.
Prepare jello with 3 cups of boiling water and add strawberries.
Layer on top.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: fruit cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Soften cream cheese, add milk and sugar and whip until fluffy.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold cheese and Dream Whip together.
Add fruit topping to cheese and whip mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill for 2 hours and serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour together.
Coat pork chops.
Brown lightly pork chops in oil.
Drain off oil.
Mix soup and rosemary leaves.
Cut potatoes in half.
Put pork chops, carrots and potatoes in pan.
Pour soup over them.
Let cook slow for approximately 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: shrimp feta ala neil
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
Cook pasta and drain.
Combine the egg and Ricotta cheese.
Stir in the parsley, salt and pepper.
Toss the warm, cooked pasta with Ricotta mixture.
Turn into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Press onto bottom and up the sides to form a crust.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Crumb flour, sugar and margarine and set aside 1 cup for topping.
Add egg, milk, soda and vanilla to the remaining crumb mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup of reserved crumbs on top of batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top next.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: almond roca
directions: Cook butter and sugar, stirring constantly until mixture is the color of peanut butter; then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into a buttered cookie sheet.
Spread grated chocolate onto the hot mixture.
Sprinkle almonds on the chocolate.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: basic 7-up pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in nonstick pan coated with butter.
Makes about six 5-inch cakes.

title: chinese cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumber in 1/2 lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds and slice thinly.
Sprinkle cucumber with salt and let stand about 30 minutes in a colander.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook down on low.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients but sour cream and chill for 1 hour.
Whip cream until light and mix with other ingredients.

title: crullers
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Roll out on floured board until the dough is very thin.
Cut into strips and tie like a bow.
Fry in deep cooking oil.
Sprinkle the pieces with powdered sugar.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with
onions
and celery.
Mix soup and milk. Layer
meat
and
Tater
Tots.
Pour soup mix over all. Bake
for
1 1/2 hours.
May add two (20 ounce) bags carrots, peas, broccoli or corn, if desired.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth and creamy. Chill.
Serve with your favorite fresh fruits.
Serves 12.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread the refried beans over the bottom of a 10-inch diameter plate. Spread the mashed avocados over the beans. In a small mixing bowl, combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning and mix well to blend. Spread a layer of this mix over the avocados. Follow this by a layer of the cheeses, combined. Layer the olives, tomatoes and green onion. Serve with the tortilla chips.

title: grandma atchley's fried tomato gravy
directions: Cut tomatoes in large slices and dredge in flour; salt and pepper lightly.
Place in a large frying pan with enough margarine to fry.
Fry tomatoes until brown a few minutes and turn over. Begin to stir with a wooden spoon.
Push aside and add more tomatoes.
When all are soft, add milk to make a gravy.
Let cook slowly until all tomatoes are done.
Add sugar and more salt and pepper.
Add a dash of curry.
Serve over bread or plain.

title: easy supper casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet; drain.
Stir in pasta, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cornmeal cake
directions: Melt your margarine; add your sugar, eggs and milk.
To this, add
your
Bisquick
and cornmeal; blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin chip preserves
directions: Cut slices from a fine high colored pumpkin.
Peel and cut slices into thin chips.
Of the pumpkin, take 2 cups and put into a large pan, laying 2 cups of sugar over this.
Add 1 lemon (sliced thin) and let set all night.
Early in the morning, put all of it into a preserving pan.
Add the stick of cinnamon, cloves and water.
Boil all together until the chips are clear and the syrup ???.
Boil for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars. Makes 2 half-pints.

title: delicious chicken breast
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 glass baking dish.
Preheat oven to 275 degrees.
Line baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap chicken breast with bacon and then place on top of dried beef.
Mix the soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered for 2 1/2 hours.
tags: Cream of Mushroom soup or Cream of Chicken

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onion.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients.
Dip onion in the mixture.
Cook in hot fat.

title: lebkuchen(recipe from late 1800's)
directions: Add baking soda to 1/2 cup hot water.
Combine all other ingredients except flour and mix; add soda and water gradually. Add enough flour to roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake in hot oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
This is a very old recipe.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in grated lemon rind and juice from lemon.

title: cucumber and raisin salad
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or early in day:
thinly slice unpeeled cucumbers.
In large bowl, toss cucumber slices with 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, coarsely chop walnuts.
Over medium heat, toast lightly in a small saucepan until lightly browned, stirring and shaking pan frequently.
Thinly slice green onions.
Tipping bowl over sink, press cucumbers with hand to drain as much liquid as possible. Stir in walnuts, green onions, yogurt, raisins, mint, vinegar, black pepper and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Refrigerate if not serving right away.
Makes 6 servings.
Each serving about 145 calories.

title: butter 'n stuffing tomatoes
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery
in butter.
Add stuffing and gently toss.
Add tomatoes and cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and jars of carrots.
Beat all together.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into mixture.
Turn into round tube pan that is greased and floured. Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into quart jar over 2 to 3 buttons of fresh garlic.
Refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely.
Serve over any kind of lettuce salad.

title: moist brownies
directions: Mix all by hand until well blended and bake in glass 9 x 13-inch (large Pyrex) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: apple-pecan cake
directions: Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon warm water.
Cream shortening, dark brown and granulated sugar.
Add unbeaten egg.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and soda.
Fold in chopped apple.
Top batter with light brown sugar and pecans. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge muffins
directions: Beat together.
Add butter and chocolate.
Pour into greased or lined muffin pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine and press in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Separately,
blend sugar and cream cheese; spread over pretzels.
Spread Cool Whip over cream cheese and chill.
Then dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice and add strawberries.
Set and cool completely in refrigerator. Lastly, pour jello mixture over top and refrigerate.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill or freeze until set.
You can omit any one of the fruits above and still have a delicious salad.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saut onion, celery and green pepper in butter or margarine. Into pot, add carrots, potatoes, chicken broth, garlic, dill weed, pepper and salt.
Cook all on low until carrots and potatoes are done (about 30 minutes).
Add corn, half and half and salmon.
Heat and serve.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix well by hand.
Divide into 6 muffins and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You can substitute raisins for the prunes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into 1 gallon electric freezer.
It takes about 45 minutes to 1 hour to freeze.
Eat plain or with your favorite toppings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water overnight in large pot (Dutch oven).
To cook, allow 4 to 5 hours.
Saute ham and sausage in pan.
Add onion, celery, parsley and garlic.
When thin, add all to pot. Add bay leaves and hot sauce.
Boil gently, stirring occasionally, until beans are soft and creamy.
Mash a few beans on pot side with spoon to cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Freezes well.

title: 7 layer spectacular squares
directions: Melt stick of margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the graham cracker crumbs on top.
Pack them.
Sprinkle the coconut on evenly, then a layer of finely chopped nuts, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips.
Pour over this the condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cut into squares.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in butter or oil.
Add chilies and chicken.
Stir until heated.
Add soup and sour cream.
Cook until heated.
Fill tortillas with a spoonful of mixture.
Roll and place seam side down in an oblong pan.
Cover all the tortillas with leftover sauce; sprinkle with salsa and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Roll out soft bread or pizza dough. Brush down center 1/2 of the following:
egg and Parmesan cheese. Place down center meats and cheese, sliced from deli.
Add onions and peppers, cooked or uncooked.
Fold over one side and repeat, if desired.
Fold over remaining side and seal ends.
Brush on remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: praline grahams
directions: Combine butter and sugar in sauce pan on medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes stirring constantly.
Break graham crackers in 1/2 and arrange on cookie sheet.
Spoon mixture on crackers.
Heat oven to 300 degrees.
Cook for 12 minutes.

title: donna's decadent dessert
directions: Layer rolls in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla together; spread on layer of rolls.
Top with second can of rolls.
Make holes in top; drizzle melted margarine.
Top with cinnamon and sugar mixed together. Bake according to crescent roll package directions.

title: "smashed up" spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in saucepan or skillet.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until soft.
Crumble in the beef.
Stir and fry until meat loses red color.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour in tomatoes and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Break spaghetti in pieces, sprinkle in a little at a time, stirring it into the sauce and keeping it separated.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, stir occasionally.
Serve with cheese.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar and oleo in bowl with a pastry blender. Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Beat egg and add to mix.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk (large bowl).
Add flour mix and vanilla to liquid.
Stir.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Sprinkle reserved mix on each plus cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Can freeze after baking.)

title: meat balls
directions: Form into balls size of walnuts.
Pour sauce over and brown in oven.

title: fruit marshmallow salad
directions: This beautiful salad by itself can be the main part of a lunch of supper menu if you choose to serve it with cottage cheese. Otherwise, it makes a great accompaniment to barbecue chicken, roasted Cornish game hens or a game dinner.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add carrots, onion and celery.
Saute over low heat until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Stir in chicken broth.
Add milk and make a smooth sauce.
Add soda and the cheese finely cut in small pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir constantly over low heat while cheese is melting to avoid scorching.
Add parsley before serving.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat in microwave so honey will blend in with soy sauce.
Great for marinating beef, chicken and fish. Great for barbecue grills after marinating.

title: ham balls
directions: Form ham loaf into balls and place in a baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small sauce pan, mix brown sugar, ketchup, soy sauce, dry mustard and pineapple.
Heat on medium.
Mix water and cornstarch together.
Add to pineapple mixture until bubbly and thickened.
Then add to ham balls and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: old-time starter
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a stone crock or bowl.
Mix well.
Add water and beat to a smooth batter.
Cover with cheesecloth; set in a warm place until thoroughly sour.
You determine this by the yeastly smell, usually takes about 12 hours. This Starter gathers yeast from the air to provide leavening. Keep in refrigerator.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl combine egg and 1/4 cup of the tomato soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture in small balls.
Place in 10-inch skillet.
Mix remaining soup with water and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir often.

title: southern chicken
directions: Combine butter and garlic, set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; stir well.

Dip each chicken breast in butter mixture and coat with bread crumb mixture, roll tightly, staring at narrow end, and secure with a wooden pick. Arrange rolls in a shallow baking pan, drizzle with remaining butter and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, vanilla, eggs and sugar; sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix liquid mixture with dry mixture.
Dice and fold in 3 cups apples.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes. Line cookie sheet (10 x 15-inches).
Line with foil and whole graham crackers. Pour butter-sugar mixture over crackers and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
After baking, cut immediately and remove from pan.
Place on foil and let cool.

title: tomato and zucchini gratin
directions: In a large frying pan over medium heat, saute the onion in the oil for 2 minutes.
Add the zucchini; saute until tender, about 4 minutes.
Stir in the thyme and basil.
Remove from the heat. Coat a 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray.
Layer half of the rice in the dish.
Top with 1/2 of the zucchini and 1/2 of the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until heated through and lightly browned.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix boiling water, molasses and soda.
Add to dry ingredients. Sprinkle crumbs on top of batter.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: light vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, pour tomato juice, water, shredded cabbage, broth and onion.
Simmer 30 minutes and then add all other ingredients.
Continue cooking another 30 minutes.

title: skroodles
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water.
Saute onion in skillet.
Add ground chuck and fry until brown.
Drain, add spices and mix with soup and sauce.
Mix drained macaroni with the meat/sauce mixture. Serves 4.

title: eileen's cookies
directions: Take 2 vanilla wafers and put apricot filling between and dip in Cool Whip. Roll in coconut. Freeze before you eat them.

title: disaster salad
directions: Fold in all ingredients.
Cherries and nuts are optional.

title: cheese apples
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, add cheese and flour.
Put apples in buttered 9x13 baking dish.
Pour mixture over apples. Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.
(Very good served with Chicken Rotel main dish.)

title: orange tapioca jell-o
directions: Boil water, add Jell-O, stir; add tapioca mix, continue to cook until thickened (3 - 4 minutes).

title: kale soup
directions: Cook macaroni; set aside. Add all the other ingredients together. When cooked, add macaroni rings and serve.

title: date balls
directions: Cook all in pan until bubbly.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix.
Cool. Make into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Fold into egg whites.
Cook on a lightly greased griddle.

title: swordfish with mustard-basil butter
directions: Mix butter, mustard and basil.
Brush fish with oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Grill fish 5 minutes on each side.
Top with a spoonful of butter.
Garnish with basil sprigs.

title: great coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Combine dry ingredients.
Take out 3/4 cup for top.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix into pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup topping.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: german tossed salad
directions: Place ingredients in a large salad bowl or 8 x 15-inch dish in order given.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Scoop all the way to the bottom of dish when serving to get all layers.

title: orange grecian cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixer.
Turn on mixer and stir on low for 4 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip icebox cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together the shortening and sugars. Add beaten eggs and blend.
In second bowl, sift together dry ingredients. Add half of the dry mixture to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Add rest of dry ingredients.
Mix well. Form into small loaves and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, slice and place on cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: super cherry dessert
directions: Line a 9-inch square dish with graham cracker squares. Filling into cover the bottom.

title: quick chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces.
Spray large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables, onion and carrots; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Cover; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender and internal juices of chicken run clear.
Stir in hoisin sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve chicken and vegetables over hot cooked rice.
Garnish with fresh cilantro, if desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown together first 3 ingredients; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; mix all together.
Bake for 1/2 hour or you can use crock-pot.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix sugar, butter and eggs together. Add molasses.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Alternate buttermilk and flour to other liquids.
Bake in loaf or Bundt pan until nicely browned.

title: polish drumsticks
directions: First Layer:
Mix together vanilla wafers, melted butter and salted peanuts.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; refrigerate until partially set. Whip well.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together well, then mix with Jell-O.
Set aside.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Combine mixtures with vanilla in large bowl and beat well.
Pour into graham cracker crust in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: good brunswick stew(you need a large pot)
directions: You can double this recipe and freeze.

title: avocado dip
directions: Cut avocado into halves; remove seed and skin.
Sieve by forcing fruit through.
Rub bowl with garlic and discard garlic. Add avocado with other ingredients; blend well.
Chill.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: dorothy's dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Chill.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Put corn and water in freezer bag.
Leave top open.
Microwave 4 minutes at full power.
Put butter and salt on corn, if desired.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix salt and flour; cut oleo and potatoes into flour, adding milk gradually.
Mix well and drop on cookie sheet in biscuit size drops (from spoon).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Butter and serve hot.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash in water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients to squash and cook in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and dry taco seasoning in bowl. Turn into pie plate and refrigerate.
Just before serving, top with shredded lettuce, cheese and sauce or salsa.
You may add diced fresh tomato on top as well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apples with honey sauce(modern)
directions: Pare and core apples.
Mix flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; mix to form soft dough.
Roll dough into 12 x 8-inch rectangle; cut into 6 squares.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Let rise in mixing bowl until approximately doubled in bulk.
Place on floured board and knead.
Make into rolls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.

title: nonnie's chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken breasts on each side in small amount of oil. Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup, water, rice and spices. Mix well. Pour mixture in a 4-quart casserole dish. Arrange chicken breasts on top. Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. May add more liquid halfway through cooking if needed.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; sprinkle over pineapple. Sprinkle grated cheese over this.
Sprinkle crumbled Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork roast with orange glaze
directions: Mix salt, m.s.g., thyme, dry mustard and ginger together. Place roast on rack in roasting pan. Rub spice mixture on pork roast.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours (or 30 minutes per pound) or until meat thermometer registers 185°.

title: witches brew
directions: Soda and juice should be chilled.
In punch bowl, combine milk and pineapple juice; add orange soda.
Top with scoops of orange sherbet.
Refrigerate.
Use plastic pumpkin to serve for Halloween party.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix everything together except for the eggs and milk. Keep 2 cups of the mixture back for the top of cake. Beat eggs and milk together, then mix into the cake mixture. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with the rest of the cake mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: best broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli and cheese.
Pour dressing over all. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix in bacon before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. Top with corn chips, shredded cheese, sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce. Yields 16 servings.

title: squash elegant
directions: Slice squash.
Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Simmer squash and onions until tender.
Stir together the soup, sour cream, chestnuts and pimientos.
Drain squash and fold into soup mixture. Melt margarine and drizzle over stuffing mix.
Place half of stuffing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add squash mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese during last 10 minutes.

title: french bean salad
directions: Drain all beans thoroughly.
Heat sugar, vinegar, olive oil, salt, pepper and onion.
Bring to boil;
pour over beans. Stir and let stand overnight.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream butter with salt; gradually add part of the sugar, blending after each addition.
Add remaining sugar, alternately with milk, beating vigorously after each addition until smooth and creamy and of proper spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla. Makes enough to cover tops and sides of 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour, or until set.
Serves 12 to 14.
Can be halved.
If so, use 3 eggs.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight, then drain and rinse.
In your soup pot, fry bacon, then discard.
Saute onions and celery.
Then add chicken broth.
Grate potato and carrot into the broth.
Add bouillon and pepper.
Add beans and water to fill up your pot to where you want it.
Bring to a boil.
Let it boil for at least 15 minutes, then turn heat down.
Cover, then simmer until done (2 to 3 hours).
Navy, Northern or pinto beans will do; can be mixed, also.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Blend in milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; cool.
Top with strawberry preserves; chill.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger; add Manwich sauce.
Put 1 can of crescent rolls in bottom of a 13 x 10-inch pan.
Add hamburger mixture. Sprinkle in Cheddar cheese on top, then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with 1 can of crescent rolls.
Bake at temperature on roll can.

title: awesome omelette
directions: Preheat oven 10 minutes at 325°.
Melt butter in quiche dish in oven for 5 minutes.
Chop sausage into small pieces.
Scramble eggs slightly and add milk.
Mix a little more.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until eggs are set, peeling away from side of dish.
Turn off oven.
Cover with cheese.
Leave in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve.
Serves 4.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix and pat into 9-inch pie plate.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or unti slightly browned.
Cool.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Mix peanut butter, butter and vanilla in separate bowl; gradually add sugar and cream until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well each time.
Blend in flour mix.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour mix into an 8-inch greased pan. Cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until the center is firm.
Cool 5 minutes after removed.

title: cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Form dough into balls and press with fork. Bake less than 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine, add salt and sugar, gradually and one egg at a time, beating well.
Add lemon rind, milk, flour and baking powder.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes.
While loaf is still hot, spoon over bread the juice of one lemon and 1/2 c. sugar that has been brought to a boil enough to dissolve sugar.
This is delicious! And the secret is in performing the last operation while everything is hot!

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Combine milk with egg; stir in shortening.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly; stir in apples and raisins.
Add liquid mixture, and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix. Batter should be lumpy.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and put in casserole dish.
Stew chicken breasts until cooked.
Cool, bone, skin and cut meat into bite-sized chunks.
Put on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and margarine mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
May be refrigerated prior to baking but will need to bake longer.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine apples and water in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. Mash.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Quickly pour into hot jars, filling to 1/4-inch from top; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Yields 6 pints.

title: new orleans shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Cut shrimp in half.
Mix shrimp, rice, vegetables and lemon juice.
Now, add remaining seasonings and mayonnaise.
Stir carefully.
Serve with crisp greens.
Garnish with tomato wedges and boiled egg quarters, if desired.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Add celery and bell peppers.
Let stand 20 minutes longer.
Drain well.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Cool.
Put in freezer containers and seal.
Label and date, then freeze.
Thaw and serve with your favorite meals.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil cabbage 10 minutes; drain and place in baking dish.
Blend soup, cheese and milk until cheese melts, then pour over cabbage.
Put buttered bread crumbs over cabbage mixture. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Cut cake into small pieces.
Put 1/2 into bottom of punch bowl.
Pour 1 box of prepared pudding over cake.
Add 1 can pineapple and spread over pudding.
Next spread 1 can pie filling, 1/2 container Cool Whip, 1/2 can coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Repeat layers, making 2 complete layers.
Will fill small punch bowl.

title: strawberry pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix milk, jello and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and sliced strawberries.
(Can add a little sugar or Sweet & Low if strawberries are not sweet.)
Pour inot graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except peaches.
Pour into 8 x 11-inch ovenproof shallow pan.
Top with peaches and bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
(Cobbler will still be slightly runny.)
Let set for 15 minutes and serve warm or place in containers and pack for lunch.
Makes 6 servings.
(I put some of the peach juice in with the peaches; this is real good and easy.)

title: home pastry mix
directions: This will keep in airtight can on shelf.
Put flour and salt into large bowl.
Cut in shortening until like peas.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; put onion and bell pepper in Pyrex dish.
Mix all other ingredients, then pour butter mixture in.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: Beat oil into mayonnaise. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Chill before serving, Store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream fig cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix figs, nuts, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs.
Gently beat in sour cream and vanilla; blend in flour mixture.
Pour in oiled Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: neapolitan ziti
directions: Bake or pan-fry sausage links until fully cooked.
Drain.
Cool sufficiently to be able to cut them.
Core and clean bell peppers of seed and membranes and cut into strips.
Cut sausage links in half lengthwise, then cut the split sausage into 1/2-inch slices. Saute the bell pepper slices in olive oil over moderate heat until crispness is lost.
Prepare the Salsa Marinara.
Makes 5 cups.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, 3/4 teaspoon baking soda, cream of tartar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Set aside.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening and molasses.
Add beaten egg, cinnamon, ginger and soda in water.
Mix.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook, bone and cut chicken into pieces.
Stir chicken, soups, sour cream and almonds together in a bowl.
Pour chicken mixture into a large greased baking dish (8 x 11 or 9 x 13-inch).
Stir the melted butter, poppy seed and crackers together to make topping. Spread topping on top of chicken mixture. Bake
at 350° until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by 1/4 cup onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread into pumpkin shape. Add a bit more dough to form stem.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cookies are firm and lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Decorate using icing or peanut butter to affix assorted candies, raisins, nuts, etc.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and whole orange (remove seeds first). Add 2 cups of sugar and let stand.
Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water, let cool.
Combine all ingredients and put in large or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Break into thirds before boiling.
Rinse noodles with cold water and drain.
Grate carrots.
Chop or dice remaining veggies.
Toss together with noodles.
Add salad supreme (whole bottle), salt and pepper, and Italian dressing. Refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and spoon into a greased casserole dish. In a mixing bowl, combine crushed crackers with margarine, mix well and put on top of vegetable mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until slightly bubbly and crisp. Serves 6 to 8. Recipe can be halved.

title: home on the range(drink)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Leave for 24 hours.
Strain.
Chill before serving and do not add ice.
This mixture can be kept indefinitely, growing more potent each day.
"Tastes wild; kicks violently."

title: sweet and sour wrap-ups
directions: Cut bacon crosswise into thirds.
Cut small water chestnuts in half and larger ones in thirds.
Wrap 1 piece of bacon around each water chestnut.
Secure bacon with wood toothpicks.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp (do not overcook).
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over bacon.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 to 30 minutes, basting once or twice.
Serve hot.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: picante-dijon grilled chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Combine picante sauce, sugar and mustard; mix well.
Place chicken on grill over hot coals or on rack of broiler pan about 6 inches from heat; brush generously with picante sauce mixture.
Grill or broil about 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Sprinkle sauce to taste.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sand cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg gradually.
Stir in almonds and flour.
Wrap in plastic and let rest in refrigerator for one hour.
Remove from refrigerator and roll out into long cylinder, about 2 inches in diameter.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Press out with a fork.
Lay on ungreased cookie sheets and bake for 10 minutes until lightly browned around edges.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Grate some chocolate squares on top of cake.

title: caramel toffee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine softened butter, cake mix, eggs, and water. Beat until smooth.
Stir in brickle bits and chocolate chips. Drop cookie dough from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.
I make each mound of dough about the size of a golf ball. This makes a good size cookie.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the cookies are lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet onto rack to cool. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: canned pickled beets
directions: Wash beets.
Cook beets until tender; cool.
Peel and cut larger ones into quarters, making most of them the same size.
In a big pot, cook the beets and all of the ingredients for 10 minutes. Pack the beets in canning jars and seal.
This makes about 6 quarts.
Repeat this recipe until all beets and juice are canned. One bushel of beets makes 46 pints.
You can double this recipe and do more at one time.

title: quelites(spinach)
directions: Wash
the
spinach and cook 15 minutes or until tender. Fry chopped
onions
and bacon in butter.
Add spinach, salt, vinegar and chili seed.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread).
Can be put in hollowed bread to serve.
Best if made the day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: fried shrimp balls
directions: Mince shrimp as finely as possible.
Combine shrimp, chestnuts, cornstarch, sherry, onion powder and egg.
Blend well.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Lower shrimp balls into hot oil with slotted spoon.
Fry about 5 minutes until balls turn golden brown. Keep warm in chafing dish or serve on wooden picks.
Makes about 15 balls.

title: pickled eggs or red beet eggs(penna. dutch)
directions: Put all ingredients together except the eggs and boil for 5 minutes.
Put eggs in a 1 gallon jar and cover with the hot mixture.
It takes 4 to 5 days to pickle.
Turn eggs on occasion.

title: grilled zucchini(barbecue or foreman grill)
directions: Slice zucchini lengthways (6 slices each).
Place in dish with balsamic vinegar.
Cover and let sit for at least 30 minutes. (If time allows, cover and refrigerate for up to 2 hours.)
Place marinated zucchini slices on hot grill for 2 minutes.
Flip slices and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over slices.
Close grill for 2 minutes.
Promptly remove and serve.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Make pastry for 2 crust 8-inch pie.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon together.
Mix lightly through fruit.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 375° to 400° until juice begins to bubble through slits and crust is nicely brown. Serve while warm.

title: wiener bean pot
directions: Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter, cheese and soup together.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, celery, onions and rice.
Add cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange yogurt ice pops
directions: Spoon yogurt and orange juice in alternate layers into 8 paper cups (4 ounce size).
Freeze about 1 hour, until semi firm. Insert popsicle stick in center of each.
Freeze several hours or overnight until firm (see note).
Peel paper from ice pops before serving.
Makes 8 pops.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pickle juice.
Cool; refrigerate until begins to thicken.
Whip with rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Cream the cheese in with chopped peaches and nuts.
Mix in with jello.
Pour in 1-quart container.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add beaten eggs.
Mix good. Add raw rhubarb.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell, then bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts in a heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until a few drops of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cool water.
Take off heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coloring.
Beat until mixture is creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or foil.
Let cool. Yields 25 to 30 patties.

title: lamb with baked potatoes(lahum bil saneeyee)
directions: Alternate layers of lamb, potatoes and onions in well buttered baking pan and dot with butter.
Pour tomato puree on top and add seasonings.
Bake in slow oven, 250°, for about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil zucchini and water until soft (approximately 20 minutes).
Add Sure-Jell and bring to a hard-boil.
Add sugar and pineapple; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Stir well and put in jars.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skin.
Peel and grate.
Grate cheese; heat margarine and chicken soup.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream. Butter the bottom and sides of casserole dish.
Put layer of potatoes, onions and cheese.
Add sauce.
Repeat 2 or 3 layers. Salt to taste.
Crush corn flakes and cover top of casserole with flakes and 2 or 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Pour over top.
Cook for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Rinse peas with cold water and drain well.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Combine oil, vinegar, cayenne pepper and mayonnaise. Pour over peas.
Stir gently.
Chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
At serving time, add diced tomato.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; add water to syrup to make 2 cups. Heat to a boil. Add cherry Jell-O to liquid and stir until it dissolves. Put into dish and set in icebox.

title: hamburger minestrone soup
directions: Brown beef and onions until just slightly brown.
While beef is browning, add water and soup mix in soup kettle and mix well. Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then add beef and onions.
Simmer for 1 hour.
You can sprinkle with cheese when serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: nachos grande
directions: In saucepan, stir soup and milk.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Make layers of chips, soup and salsa.
Top with sliced green onions, sliced jalapeno peppers and guacamole, if desired.

title: plants delight
directions: Mix ingredients together in a jar with a cover. Place on plants every 2 weeks.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
In Pour in coleslaw dressing right before serving and mix well.

title: toffee treasure cake or heath bar cake
directions: Generously grease and lightly flour 9 or 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon; set aside.
No need to sift flour.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients except nuts, candy bars and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Spoon remaining batter into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture, then with nuts, crushed candy bars.
Pour 1/4 cup melted margarine over batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until top springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix peaches and sugar in blender.
Add mixture to other ingredients.
Churn until frozen.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into shell.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms; remove stems and set caps aside.
Chop stems fine.
Melt butter; add stems, onion and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add flour, then moisten with tomato juice, no more than 1 to 2 tablespoons.
Stir in nutmeg, parsley or basil, celery seed, meat or cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cool.
Fill caps with mixture, rounding well over tops.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: katie's noodles
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add salt and water.
Beat again until light.
Add flour, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Mix with fork until ball forms.
Divide in two roll-outs.
Add flour as needed.
Roll on towel to dry.
Cut.
Cook 3 to 8 minutes in boiling broth or water.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: berardi pasta
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add chicken and cook until tender.
Add cooked sausage (cut into bite sized pieces) and broccoli and saute until broccoli is tender.
Add dried tomatoes, seasonings, wine, broth and butter.
Simmer 5 minutes and toss onto cooked pasta. If desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: pudding eclair
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease well a 10 x 15 inch jellyroll pan, or cookie sheet with low sides, with shortening. Combine water and butter in saucepan and bring to hard boil with all butter melted. Remove from heat. Drop in flour and stir vigorously with a wooden spoon. Add eggs one at a time, beating with spoon until smooth after each egg. Spread into cookie sheet and up the sides. Bake 30 minutes and cool completely.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, 1/4 cup flour and sugar together and place into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Put on top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions.
Add sugar, vinegar, peppers, spice and salt.
Cook slowly until thick.

title: turkey broccoli divan
directions: Bake, bone and slice turkey into 1-inch cubes.
Wrap in foil. Place in pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cooked.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix
according to directions on box and bake 1/2 the
batter
in
x
13-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Take out of oven.
Melt caramels, oleo and evaporated milk over cake.
Sprinkle
chocolate chips and nuts on top. Pour remaining batter over
and
bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add the vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in the chopped apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
When cool, slice and top with whipped topping to serve.

title: cooked pineapple
directions: Grease pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Pour over pineapple.
Add cheese, top with crackers and drizzle with butter over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned west virginia blackberry jam cake
directions: Blend sugar, spices, salt, soda, baking powder and flour. Add milk, shortening and eggs after well blended. Blend together until creamy. Add jam (or preserves). Turn into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until cake has slightly left the pan around the sides. Nuts may be added if you wish.

title: peas and carrots in thyme sauce
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, melt margarine.
Cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Add peas and carrots.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese together; then add powdered sugar and half and half.
After all is well mixed, add the Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust and freeze for 2 hours.
Be sure and take pie out of freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: merry christmas punch
directions: Combine orange and lemon rinds, water and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Stir in almond extract and fruit juice.
Pour over ice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Yields about 1 1/4 gallons.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Use a shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine in dish. Add remaining ingredients to melted margarine and mix.
Cover with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake until brown.

title: beef curry
directions: Heat oil in large pot; add beef and brown.
Mix flour and curry powder and add to beef.
Cook approximately 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until well thickened.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix well and shape into balls.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Place on broiler pan and bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: chiffon sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks and add remainder of ingredients.
In another bowl, mix egg whites with 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until it forms peaks.
Fold into other mixture.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes and 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple, cheese and 1/2 stick margarine. Pour into baking dish.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all together lightly.
Bake in greased muffin tins in a 375° oven for approximately 20 minutes.
Can keep dough in refrigerator for several weeks.
Makes several dozen muffins.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool. They will become hard so you can pick up easily.

title: chinese asparagus
directions: Snap of woody base of asparagus stalk at breaking point where tender part begins.
Slice on extreme diagonal, approximately 1 1/2-inches long.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 6-quart saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a full boil over high heat.
Reduce heat. Stirring frequently, boil rapidly 40 to 50 minutes or until small amount cooled in freezer gels.
Remove from heat.
Skim and put in sterilized jars.

title: five minute blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch; stir in water.
Add 2 cups berries. Cook until thick, stirring often.
Cool.
Bake pie shells.
Put 1 cup berries in each shell.
Pour cooked filling over berries. Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: snappy turtle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Mix in butter, brown sugar, 1 egg, 1 egg yolk, vanilla and maple flavoring. Form into round shapes for turtle bodies. Dip in egg whites and insert whole pecan for turtle head and pecan halves for the feet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and almonds extract and vanilla. Add all dry ingredients.
Cream mixture.
Add sour cream and peaches.
Pour into greased 10 or 12-inch Bundt cake or tube pan.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Add flour, Jell-O, water, oil and unbeaten eggs to the cake mix in a mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed or beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and beat, until thoroughly mixed. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: corned beef casserole
